{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885284400,"sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","part":{"id":"prt_d7b02ebef001D8bRS975u49Ait","messageID":"msg_d7b02da5e001Lg1aGtsudcgFs7","sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 Design: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-018  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S (Small)\n9: \n10: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller is a Kubernetes controller that automatically deletes AgentRuntime resources that have exceeded their configured idle timeout. It monitors the `LastActivityTime` field in AgentRuntime status and compares it against the `IdleTimeoutSeconds` specified in the spec to determine when a resource should be cleaned up.\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **AgentRuntime API (pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1)**: Watches AgentRuntime resources\n14: - **client-go library**: Uses generated Kubernetes clientset for API interactions\n15: - **controller-runtime**: Manages the controller lifecycle and reconciliation loop\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### High-Level Design\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         Kubernetes Cluster                                   │\n26: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n27: │  │                         AgentRuntime Resources                          │  │\n28: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                    │  │\n29: │  │  │  Runtime 1  │  │  Runtime 2  │  │  Runtime N  │                    │  │\n30: │  │  │ (active)    │  │ (idle 20m)  │  │ (idle 45m)  │                    │  │\n31: │  │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                    │  │\n32: │  │         │                │                │                            │  │\n33: │  │         │                ▼                ▼                            │  │\n34: │  │         │         ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐                  │  │\n35: │  │         │         │ Timeout: 15m │  │ Timeout: 30m │                  │  │\n36: │  │         │         │ DELETE       │  │ DELETE       │                  │  │\n37: │  │         │         └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘                  │  │\n38: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n39: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n40: │                      Agentd Controller (Idle Cleanup)                        │\n41: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │                      Reconciliation Loop                                │  │\n43: │  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌───────────┐  │  │\n44: │  │  │    Get      │──►│   Check     │──►│  Calculate  │──►│  Delete   │  │  │\n45: │  │  │   AgentRun  │   │ IdleTimeout │   │  Remaining  │   │  if Idle  │  │  │\n46: │  │  │   time      │   │   Config    │   │   Time      │   │  Timeout  │  │  │\n47: │  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └───────────┘  │  │\n48: │  │         │                │                │                │          │  │\n49: │  │         ▼                ▼                ▼                ▼          │  │\n50: │  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n51: │  │  │                    Requeue Decision                              │  │  │\n52: │  │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐              │  │  │\n53: │  │  │  │  No Timeout │  │   Idle      │  │   Error     │              │  │  │\n54: │  │  │  │  Configured │  │   Detected  │  │   Occurred  │              │  │  │\n55: │  │  │  │  ──► Skip   │  │  ──► Delete │  │  ──► Requeue│              │  │  │\n56: │  │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘              │  │  │\n57: │  │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n58: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n59: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n60: │                      Client-Go Integration Layer                             │\n61: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n62: │  │  AgentRuntime    │  │  Typed Client    │  │  Status Subresource      │   │\n63: │  │  Interface       │  │  (v1alpha1)      │  │  (Get/Update)            │   │\n64: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │\n65: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### Component Architecture\n69: \n70: ```\n71: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n72: │                     Idle Cleanup Controller Flow                             │\n73: │                                                                              │\n74: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n75: │  │  Watch   │──►│  Reconcile│──►│   Get    │──►│  Parse   │──►│  Check   │  │\n76: │  │  Events  │   │  Request  │   │  AgentRun │   │  Timeout │   │  Activity│  │\n77: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │  time     │   │  Config  │   │  Time    │  │\n78: │                                └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n79: │                                                                     │        │\n80: │                          ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n81: │                          │                                                   │\n82: │                          ▼                                                   │\n83: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n84: │  │  Return  │◀──│  Schedule│◀──│  Delete  │◀──│  Expired │◀──│Calculate │  │\n85: │  │  Result  │   │  Requeue │   │  Resource│   │  ?       │   │Idle Time │  │\n86: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n87: │                                                                              │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### Component Interactions\n92: \n93: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n94: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n95: | **Reconciler** | Core reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime | context.Context, reconcile.Request | reconcile.Result, error |\n96: | **AgentRuntimeInterface** | Typed client for AgentRuntime CRUD | AgentRuntime objects | AgentRuntime operations |\n97: | **IdleTimeoutChecker** | Determines if resource has exceeded idle timeout | AgentRuntime status | bool (expired), time.Duration (remaining) |\n98: | **CleanupExecutor** | Performs the deletion of expired resources | AgentRuntime reference | error |\n99: | **RequeueCalculator** | Calculates next requeue time | remaining duration | reconcile.Result |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Directory Structure\n104: \n105: ```\n106: pkg/agentd/\n107: ├── controller.go         # Main reconciler implementation (~180 lines)\n108: ├── controller_test.go    # Unit tests for reconciler (~200 lines)\n109: ├── config.go             # Controller configuration (~80 lines)\n110: ├── metrics.go            # Prometheus metrics for cleanup operations (~60 lines)\n111: └── doc.go                # Package documentation (~20 lines)\n112: \n113: cmd/agentd/\n114: └── main.go               # Controller entry point (~100 lines)\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Data Structures\n120: \n121: ### Domain Types\n122: \n123: #### Reconciler\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: // Reconciler reconciles AgentRuntime objects for idle cleanup.\n127: type Reconciler struct {\n128:     // Client is the Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime resources\n129:     client client.Client\n130:     \n131:     // Scheme is the runtime scheme for type registration\n132:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n133:     \n134:     // Clock provides time functionality (allows mocking in tests)\n135:     Clock Clock\n136:     \n137:     // Metrics collects operational metrics\n138:     Metrics *Metrics\n139: }\n140: \n141: // Clock abstracts time operations for testability.\n142: type Clock interface {\n143:     Now() time.Time\n144: }\n145: \n146: // realClock implements Clock using the system clock.\n147: type realClock struct{}\n148: \n149: func (c *realClock) Now() time.Time {\n150:     return time.Now()\n151: }\n152: \n153: // NewReconciler creates a new AgentRuntime idle cleanup reconciler.\n154: func NewReconciler(client client.Client, scheme *runtime.Scheme) *Reconciler {\n155:     return &Reconciler{\n156:         Client:  client,\n157:         Scheme:  scheme,\n158:         Clock:   &realClock{},\n159:         Metrics: newMetrics(),\n160:     }\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: #### IdleTimeoutConfig\n165: \n166: ```go\n167: // IdleTimeoutConfig holds the idle timeout configuration.\n168: type IdleTimeoutConfig struct {\n169:     // DefaultTimeout is the fallback timeout when not specified in spec\n170:     DefaultTimeout time.Duration\n171:     \n172:     // MaxTimeout is the maximum allowed idle timeout\n173:     MaxTimeout time.Duration\n174:     \n175:     // MinTimeout is the minimum allowed idle timeout\n176:     MinTimeout time.Duration\n177: }\n178: \n179: // DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig returns the default configuration.\n180: func DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig() IdleTimeoutConfig {\n181:     return IdleTimeoutConfig{\n182:         DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n183:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n184:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n185:     }\n186: }\n187: \n188: // Validate checks if the configuration is valid.\n189: func (c *IdleTimeoutConfig) Validate() error {\n190:     if c.DefaultTimeout < c.MinTimeout {\n191:         return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is less than minimum %v\", \n192:             c.DefaultTimeout, c.MinTimeout)\n193:     }\n194:     if c.DefaultTimeout > c.MaxTimeout {\n195:         return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is greater than maximum %v\",\n196:             c.DefaultTimeout, c.MaxTimeout)\n197:     }\n198:     return nil\n199: }\n200: ```\n201: \n202: #### CleanupResult\n203: \n204: ```go\n205: // CleanupResult represents the outcome of a cleanup check.\n206: type CleanupResult struct {\n207:     // ShouldDelete indicates whether the resource should be deleted\n208:     ShouldDelete bool\n209:     \n210:     // Reason provides a human-readable explanation\n211:     Reason string\n212:     \n213:     // IdleDuration is how long the resource has been idle\n214:     IdleDuration time.Duration\n215:     \n216:     // TimeoutDuration is the configured timeout\n217:     TimeoutDuration time.Duration\n218:     \n219:     // RemainingTime is time until cleanup (zero if ShouldDelete)\n220:     RemainingTime time.Duration\n221: }\n222: \n223: // String returns a string representation of the result.\n224: func (r *CleanupResult) String() string {\n225:     if r.ShouldDelete {\n226:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup: %s (idle %v, timeout %v)\", \n227:             r.Reason, r.IdleDuration, r.TimeoutDuration)\n228:     }\n229:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"skip: %s (idle %v, remaining %v)\",\n230:         r.Reason, r.IdleDuration, r.RemainingTime)\n231: }\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ### Request/Response Types\n235: \n236: #### ReconcileRequest (Internal)\n237: \n238: ```go\n239: // ReconcileRequest wraps controller-runtime's reconcile.Request.\n240: type ReconcileRequest struct {\n241:     // NamespacedName identifies the AgentRuntime resource\n242:     NamespacedName types.NamespacedName\n243: }\n244: \n245: // ToControllerRuntime converts to controller-runtime request.\n246: func (r *ReconcileRequest) ToControllerRuntime() reconcile.Request {\n247:     return reconcile.Request{NamespacedName: r.NamespacedName}\n248: }\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### Internal Types\n252: \n253: #### ControllerConfig\n254: \n255: ```go\n256: // ControllerConfig contains environment-based configuration.\n257: type ControllerConfig struct {\n258:     // LeaderElection enables leader election for HA\n259:     LeaderElection bool\n260:     \n261:     // SyncPeriod is the period for full re-listing of resources\n262:     SyncPeriod time.Duration\n263:     \n264:     // WorkerCount is the number of concurrent reconcile workers\n265:     WorkerCount int\n266:     \n267:     // IdleTimeout is the default idle timeout configuration\n268:     IdleTimeout IdleTimeoutConfig\n269:     \n270:     // MetricsBindAddress is the address for metrics server (\":8080\" or \"0\" to disable)\n271:     MetricsBindAddress string\n272:     \n273:     // HealthProbeBindAddress is the address for health probes (\":8081\" or \"0\" to disable)\n274:     HealthProbeBindAddress string\n275: }\n276: \n277: // LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables.\n278: func LoadConfig() (*ControllerConfig, error) {\n279:     cfg := &ControllerConfig{\n280:         LeaderElection:         getEnvBool(\"AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION\", true),\n281:         SyncPeriod:             getEnvDuration(\"AGENTD_SYNC_PERIOD\", 10*time.Minute),\n282:         WorkerCount:            getEnvInt(\"AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT\", 1),\n283:         IdleTimeout:            DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig(),\n284:         MetricsBindAddress:     getEnvOrDefault(\"AGENTD_METRICS_BIND_ADDRESS\", \"0\"),\n285:         HealthProbeBindAddress: getEnvOrDefault(\"AGENTD_HEALTH_PROBE_BIND_ADDRESS\", \"0\"),\n286:     }\n287:     \n288:     // Override idle timeout from env if specified\n289:     if timeout := os.Getenv(\"AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT\"); timeout != \"\" {\n290:         if d, err := time.ParseDuration(timeout); err == nil {\n291:             cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout = d\n292:         } else {\n293:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT: %v\", err)\n294:         }\n295:     }\n296:     \n297:     if err := cfg.IdleTimeout.Validate(); err != nil {\n298:         return nil, err\n299:     }\n300:     \n301:     return cfg, nil\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: #### Metrics\n306: \n307: ```go\n308: // Metrics holds Prometheus metrics for the controller.\n309: type Metrics struct {\n310:     // ReconcileTotal is the total number of reconciliations\n311:     ReconcileTotal prometheus.Counter\n312:     \n313:     // ReconcileErrors is the total number of reconciliation errors\n314:     ReconcileErrors prometheus.Counter\n315:     \n316:     // CleanupTotal is the total number of successful cleanups\n317:     CleanupTotal prometheus.Counter\n318:     \n319:     // CleanupDuration is the duration of cleanup operations\n320:     CleanupDuration prometheus.Histogram\n321:     \n322:     // IdleDuration is the idle duration of cleaned resources\n323:     IdleDuration prometheus.Histogram\n324: }\n325: \n326: // newMetrics creates a new Metrics instance.\n327: func newMetrics() *Metrics {\n328:     return &Metrics{\n329:         ReconcileTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n330:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_reconcile_total\",\n331:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanup reconciliations\",\n332:         }),\n333:         ReconcileErrors: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n334:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_reconcile_errors_total\",\n335:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanup reconciliation errors\",\n336:         }),\n337:         CleanupTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n338:             Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_total\",\n339:             Help: \"Total number of idle cleanups performed\",\n340:         }),\n341:         CleanupDuration: prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n342:             Name:    \"agentd_idle_cleanup_duration_seconds\",\n343:             Help:    \"Duration of idle cleanup operations\",\n344:             Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n345:         }),\n346:         IdleDuration: prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n347:             Name:    \"agentd_idle_cleanup_idle_duration_seconds\",\n348:             Help:    \"Idle duration of cleaned resources\",\n349:             Buckets: []float64{60, 300, 600, 1800, 3600, 7200, 86400},\n350:         }),\n351:     }\n352: }\n353: \n354: // Register registers metrics with the provided registry.\n355: func (m *Metrics) Register(reg prometheus.Registerer) error {\n356:     collectors := []prometheus.Collector{\n357:         m.ReconcileTotal,\n358:         m.ReconcileErrors,\n359:         m.CleanupTotal,\n360:         m.CleanupDuration,\n361:         m.IdleDuration,\n362:     }\n363:     for _, c := range collectors {\n364:         if err := reg.Register(c); err != nil {\n365:             return err\n366:         }\n367:     }\n368:     return nil\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: ### Constants\n373: \n374: ```go\n375: // Default configuration values\n376: const (\n377:     // DefaultIdleTimeout is the default idle timeout when not specified\n378:     DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n379:     \n380:     // DefaultRequeueInterval is the default interval for requeuing when error occurs\n381:     DefaultRequeueInterval = 30 * time.Second\n382:     \n383:     // MinRequeueInterval is the minimum requeue interval\n384:     MinRequeueInterval = 5 * time.Second\n385: )\n386: \n387: // Error reasons for status updates\n388: const (\n389:     // ReasonIdleTimeout indicates cleanup due to idle timeout\n390:     ReasonIdleTimeout = \"IdleTimeoutExceeded\"\n391:     \n392:     // ReasonNoIdleConfig indicates no idle timeout configured\n393:     ReasonNoIdleConfig = \"NoIdleTimeoutConfigured\"\n394:     \n395:     // ReasonActive indicates resource is still active\n396:     ReasonActive = \"ResourceStillActive\"\n397: )\n398: \n399: // Event types\n400: const (\n401:     // EventTypeNormal indicates a normal event\n402:     EventTypeNormal = \"Normal\"\n403:     \n404:     // EventTypeWarning indicates a warning event\n405:     EventTypeWarning = \"Warning\"\n406: )\n407: \n408: // Event reasons\n409: const (\n410:     // EventReasonIdleCleanup indicates successful idle cleanup\n411:     EventReasonIdleCleanup = \"IdleCleanup\"\n412:     \n413:     // EventReasonCleanupFailed indicates failed cleanup\n414:     EventReasonCleanupFailed = \"CleanupFailed\"\n415: )\n416: ```\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ## API Contracts\n421: \n422: ### Reconciler Interface\n423: \n424: ```go\n425: // ReconcilerInterface defines the interface for AgentRuntime reconciliation.\n426: type ReconcilerInterface interface {\n427:     // Reconcile performs idle cleanup reconciliation for the given AgentRuntime.\n428:     //\n429:     // Parameters:\n430:     //   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n431:     //   - req: Reconcile request containing the AgentRuntime namespaced name\n432:     //\n433:     // Returns:\n434:     //   - reconcile.Result: Indicates whether to requeue and when\n435:     //   - error: Non-nil if reconciliation failed (triggers requeue with backoff)\n436:     //\n437:     // Behavior:\n438:     //   1. Fetch AgentRuntime from Kubernetes API\n439:     //   2. Check if IdleTimeoutSeconds is configured in spec\n440:     //   3. Parse LastActivityTime from status\n441:     //   4. Calculate idle duration\n442:     //   5. If idle duration > timeout, delete the resource\n443:     //   6. Otherwise, requeue after remaining time\n444:     Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n445: }\n446: \n447: // SetupWithManager sets up the reconciler with the controller manager.\n448: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n449:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n450:         For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n451:         WithEventFilter(predicate.GenerationChangedPredicate{}).\n452:         Complete(r)\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### Idle Timeout Checker\n457: \n458: ```go\n459: // CheckIdleTimeout determines if an AgentRuntime has exceeded its idle timeout.\n460: //\n461: // Parameters:\n462: //   - agentRuntime: The AgentRuntime to check\n463: //   - now: Current time\n464: //\n465: // Returns:\n466: //   - *CleanupResult: Result indicating whether cleanup should occur\n467: //   - error: If status fields cannot be parsed\n468: //\n469: // Logic:\n470: //   1. If IdleTimeoutSeconds is nil/0, return ShouldDelete=false (no timeout configured)\n471: //   2. If LastActivityTime is nil, use creation timestamp\n472: //   3. Calculate idleDuration = now - lastActivityTime\n473: //   4. timeoutDuration = IdleTimeoutSeconds converted to time.Duration\n474: //   5. If idleDuration >= timeoutDuration, return ShouldDelete=true\n475: //   6. Otherwise, return ShouldDelete=false with RemainingTime = timeoutDuration - idleDuration\n476: func CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, now time.Time) (*CleanupResult, error)\n477: ```\n478: \n479: ### Cleanup Executor\n480: \n481: ```go\n482: // ExecuteCleanup deletes an AgentRuntime that has exceeded its idle timeout.\n483: //\n484: // Parameters:\n485: //   - ctx: Context for the delete operation\n486: //   - client: Kubernetes client\n487: //   - agentRuntime: The AgentRuntime to delete\n488: //\n489: // Returns:\n490: //   - error: nil if deletion initiated successfully, otherwise error\n491: //\n492: // Notes:\n493: //   - Uses foreground deletion for graceful cleanup\n494: //   - Sets deletion reason annotation before deletion\n495: func ExecuteCleanup(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error\n496: ```\n497: \n498: ### Configuration Functions\n499: \n500: ```go\n501: // LoadConfig loads controller configuration from environment variables.\n502: //\n503: // Required: None (all have defaults)\n504: //\n505: // Optional environment variables:\n506: //   - AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION: Enable leader election (default: \"true\")\n507: //   - AGENTD_SYNC_PERIOD: Full re-list period (default: \"10m\")\n508: //   - AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT: Concurrent workers (default: \"1\")\n509: //   - AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT: Default idle timeout (default: \"15m\")\n510: //   - AGENTD_METRICS_BIND_ADDRESS: Metrics server address (default: \"0\")\n511: //   - AGENTD_HEALTH_PROBE_BIND_ADDRESS: Health probe address (default: \"0\")\n512: //\n513: // Returns:\n514: //   - *ControllerConfig: Loaded configuration\n515: //   - error: If configuration is invalid\n516: func LoadConfig() (*ControllerConfig, error)\n517: \n518: // GetTimeoutDuration extracts timeout duration from AgentRuntime spec.\n519: //\n520: // Returns:\n521: //   - time.Duration: The idle timeout duration\n522: //   - bool: true if timeout is configured, false otherwise\n523: func GetTimeoutDuration(spec *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec, defaults IdleTimeoutConfig) (time.Duration, bool)\n524: ```\n525: \n526: ### Metrics Functions\n527: \n528: ```go\n529: // RecordReconcile records a reconciliation attempt.\n530: func (m *Metrics) RecordReconcile()\n531: \n532: // RecordReconcileError records a reconciliation error.\n533: func (m *Metrics) RecordReconcileError()\n534: \n535: // RecordCleanup records a successful cleanup.\n536: func (m *Metrics) RecordCleanup(duration time.Duration, idleDuration time.Duration)\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Error Handling\n542: \n543: ### Error Categories and Codes\n544: \n545: | Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n546: |-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n547: | `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound` | `NOT_FOUND` | AgentRuntime was deleted | No | Return success (no requeue) |\n548: | `ErrGetAgentRuntimeFailed` | `GET_FAILED` | Failed to fetch AgentRuntime | Yes | Requeue with backoff |\n549: | `ErrParseLastActivity` | `PARSE_FAILED` | Failed to parse LastActivityTime | No | Log and skip resource |\n550: | `ErrDeleteFailed` | `DELETE_FAILED` | Deletion API call failed | Yes | Requeue with backoff |\n551: | `ErrInvalidTimeout` | `INVALID_TIMEOUT` | IdleTimeoutSeconds invalid | No | Log and skip resource |\n552: \n553: ### Sentinel Errors\n554: \n555: ```go\n556: // Controller errors\n557: var (\n558:     ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound = errors.New(\"agentruntime: resource not found\")\n559:     ErrGetAgentRuntimeFailed = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to get resource\")\n560:     ErrParseLastActivity = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to parse last activity time\")\n561:     ErrDeleteFailed = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to delete resource\")\n562:     ErrInvalidTimeout = errors.New(\"agentruntime: invalid idle timeout configuration\")\n563: )\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ### Error Structures\n567: \n568: ```go\n569: // ReconcileError represents a reconciliation error with context.\n570: type ReconcileError struct {\n571:     // Code is the machine-readable error code\n572:     Code string `json:\"code\"`\n573:     \n574:     // Message is the human-readable error message\n575:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n576:     \n577:     // Resource is the namespaced name of the affected resource\n578:     Resource types.NamespacedName `json:\"resource\"`\n579:     \n580:     // Retryable indicates if the error is retryable\n581:     Retryable bool `json:\"retryable\"`\n582:     \n583:     // underlying is the wrapped error\n584:     underlying error\n585: }\n586: \n587: // Error returns the error string.\n588: func (e *ReconcileError) Error() string {\n589:     if e.underlying != nil {\n590:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (resource: %s): %v\", \n591:             e.Code, e.Message, e.Resource, e.underlying)\n592:     }\n593:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (resource: %s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Resource)\n594: }\n595: \n596: // Unwrap returns the wrapped error.\n597: func (e *ReconcileError) Unwrap() error {\n598:     return e.underlying\n599: }\n600: \n601: // IsRetryable returns true if the error is retryable.\n602: func (e *ReconcileError) IsRetryable() bool {\n603:     return e.Retryable\n604: }\n605: \n606: // NewReconcileError creates a new ReconcileError.\n607: func NewReconcileError(code, message string, resource types.NamespacedName, retryable bool, underlying error) *ReconcileError {\n608:     return &ReconcileError{\n609:         Code:       code,\n610:         Message:    message,\n611:         Resource:   resource,\n612:         Retryable:  retryable,\n613:         underlying: underlying,\n614:     }\n615: }\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ### Error Handling Patterns\n619: \n620: #### Reconcile Error Handling\n621: \n622: ```go\n623: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n624:     r.Metrics.RecordReconcile()\n625:     \n626:     log := log.FromContext(ctx).WithValues(\"agentruntime\", req.NamespacedName)\n627:     \n628:     // Fetch AgentRuntime\n629:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n630:     if err := r.client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n631:         if errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n632:             log.Info(\"AgentRuntime not found, skipping\")\n633:             return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n634:         }\n635:         r.Metrics.RecordReconcileError()\n636:         return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n637:             \"GET_FAILED\",\n638:             \"failed to get AgentRuntime\",\n639:             req.NamespacedName,\n640:             true,\n641:             err,\n642:         )\n643:     }\n644:     \n645:     // Check idle timeout\n646:     result, err := r.checkAndCleanup(ctx, agentRuntime)\n647:     if err != nil {\n648:         r.Metrics.RecordReconcileError()\n649:         reconcileErr, ok := err.(*ReconcileError)\n650:         if ok && !reconcileErr.IsRetryable() {\n651:             log.Error(err, \"Non-retryable error during cleanup, skipping\")\n652:             return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n653:         }\n654:         return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: DefaultRequeueInterval}, err\n655:     }\n656:     \n657:     return result, nil\n658: }\n659: ```\n660: \n661: #### Check and Cleanup Pattern\n662: \n663: ```go\n664: func (r *Reconciler) checkAndCleanup(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n665:     log := log.FromContext(ctx)\n666:     \n667:     // Check idle timeout\n668:     cleanupResult, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, r.Clock.Now())\n669:     if err != nil {\n670:         return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n671:             \"PARSE_FAILED\",\n672:             \"failed to check idle timeout\",\n673:             types.NamespacedName{Name: agentRuntime.Name, Namespace: agentRuntime.Namespace},\n674:             false,\n675:             err,\n676:         )\n677:     }\n678:     \n679:     log.V(1).Info(\"Idle check result\", \"result\", cleanupResult.String())\n680:     \n681:     // If should delete, execute cleanup\n682:     if cleanupResult.ShouldDelete {\n683:         start := r.Clock.Now()\n684:         if err := ExecuteCleanup(ctx, r.client, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n685:             return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n686:                 \"DELETE_FAILED\",\n687:                 \"failed to delete idle AgentRuntime\",\n688:                 types.NamespacedName{Name: agentRuntime.Name, Namespace: agentRuntime.Namespace},\n689:                 true,\n690:                 err,\n691:             )\n692:         }\n693:         \n694:         duration := r.Clock.Now().Sub(start)\n695:         r.Metrics.RecordCleanup(duration, cleanupResult.IdleDuration)\n696:         log.Info(\"Deleted idle AgentRuntime\",\n697:             \"idleDuration\", cleanupResult.IdleDuration,\n698:             \"timeoutDuration\", cleanupResult.TimeoutDuration)\n699:         \n700:         return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n701:     }\n702:     \n703:     // Requeue after remaining time\n704:     if cleanupResult.RemainingTime > 0 {\n705:         // Add small buffer to avoid race conditions\n706:         requeueAfter := cleanupResult.RemainingTime + MinRequeueInterval\n707:         log.V(1).Info(\"Requeuing for next idle check\",\n708:             \"requeueAfter\", requeueAfter,\n709:             \"remainingTime\", cleanupResult.RemainingTime)\n710:         return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: requeueAfter}, nil\n711:     }\n712:     \n713:     return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n714: }\n715: ```\n716: \n717: ---\n718: \n719: ## Testing Strategy\n720: \n721: ### Unit Tests\n722: \n723: #### controller_test.go\n724: \n725: ```go\n726: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NotFound(t *testing.T) {\n727:     // Setup\n728:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().Build()\n729:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n730:     \n731:     // Execute - resource doesn't exist\n732:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n733:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n734:     })\n735:     \n736:     // Assert\n737:     require.NoError(t, err)\n738:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n739:     assert.Equal(t, time.Duration(0), result.RequeueAfter)\n740: }\n741: \n742: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NoIdleTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n743:     // Setup - AgentRuntime without idle timeout\n744:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n745:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n746:             Name:      \"test\",\n747:             Namespace: \"default\",\n748:         },\n749:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n750:             // IdleTimeoutSeconds not set\n751:         },\n752:     }\n753:     \n754:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n755:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n756:     \n757:     // Execute\n758:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n759:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n760:     })\n761:     \n762:     // Assert - should not requeue, no timeout configured\n763:     require.NoError(t, err)\n764:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n765:     \n766:     // Verify resource still exists\n767:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n768:     require.NoError(t, err)\n769: }\n770: \n771: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_IdleTimeoutNotExpired(t *testing.T) {\n772:     // Setup\n773:     now := time.Now()\n774:     lastActivity := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-5 * time.Minute)) // 5 minutes ago\n775:     \n776:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n777:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n778:             Name:      \"test\",\n779:             Namespace: \"default\",\n780:         },\n781:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n782:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n783:         },\n784:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n785:             LastActivityTime: &lastActivity,\n786:         },\n787:     }\n788:     \n789:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n790:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n791:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n792:     \n793:     // Execute\n794:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n795:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n796:     })\n797:     \n798:     // Assert - should requeue after ~10 minutes\n799:     require.NoError(t, err)\n800:     assert.InDelta(t, 10*time.Minute, result.RequeueAfter, float64(time.Minute))\n801:     \n802:     // Verify resource still exists\n803:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n804:     require.NoError(t, err)\n805: }\n806: \n807: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_IdleTimeoutExpired(t *testing.T) {\n808:     // Setup\n809:     now := time.Now()\n810:     lastActivity := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-30 * time.Minute)) // 30 minutes ago\n811:     \n812:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n813:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n814:             Name:      \"test\",\n815:             Namespace: \"default\",\n816:         },\n817:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n818:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n819:         },\n820:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n821:             LastActivityTime: &lastActivity,\n822:         },\n823:     }\n824:     \n825:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n826:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n827:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n828:     \n829:     // Execute\n830:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n831:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n832:     })\n833:     \n834:     // Assert - should not requeue, resource deleted\n835:     require.NoError(t, err)\n836:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n837:     \n838:     // Verify resource deleted\n839:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n840:     require.Error(t, err)\n841:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n842: }\n843: \n844: func TestReconciler_Reconcile_NoLastActivityTime(t *testing.T) {\n845:     // Setup - no LastActivityTime, should use creation time\n846:     now := time.Now()\n847:     creationTime := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-20 * time.Minute))\n848:     \n849:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n850:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n851:             Name:              \"test\",\n852:             Namespace:         \"default\",\n853:             CreationTimestamp: creationTime,\n854:         },\n855:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n856:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n857:         },\n858:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n859:             // LastActivityTime not set\n860:         },\n861:     }\n862:     \n863:     client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n864:     reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n865:     reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n866:     \n867:     // Execute\n868:     result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n869:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n870:     })\n871:     \n872:     // Assert - should delete based on creation time\n873:     require.NoError(t, err)\n874:     assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n875:     \n876:     // Verify resource deleted\n877:     err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n878:     require.Error(t, err)\n879:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n880: }\n881: \n882: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_NoTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n883:     now := time.Now()\n884:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n885:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n886:             // IdleTimeoutSeconds not set\n887:         },\n888:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n889:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-1 * time.Hour)},\n890:         },\n891:     }\n892:     \n893:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n894:     require.NoError(t, err)\n895:     assert.False(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n896:     assert.Equal(t, \"no idle timeout configured\", result.Reason)\n897: }\n898: \n899: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_NotExpired(t *testing.T) {\n900:     now := time.Now()\n901:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n902:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n903:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](1800), // 30 minutes\n904:         },\n905:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n906:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-10 * time.Minute)},\n907:         },\n908:     }\n909:     \n910:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n911:     require.NoError(t, err)\n912:     assert.False(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n913:     assert.InDelta(t, 20*time.Minute, result.RemainingTime, float64(time.Second))\n914: }\n915: \n916: func TestCheckIdleTimeout_Expired(t *testing.T) {\n917:     now := time.Now()\n918:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n919:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n920:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](600), // 10 minutes\n921:         },\n922:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n923:             LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-15 * time.Minute)},\n924:         },\n925:     }\n926:     \n927:     result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n928:     require.NoError(t, err)\n929:     assert.True(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n930:     assert.Equal(t, \"idle timeout exceeded\", result.Reason)\n931:     assert.InDelta(t, 15*time.Minute, result.IdleDuration, float64(time.Second))\n932: }\n933: \n934: // fakeClock implements Clock for testing\n935: type fakeClock struct {\n936:     now time.Time\n937: }\n938: \n939: func (c *fakeClock) Now() time.Time {\n940:     return c.now\n941: }\n942: ```\n943: \n944: #### config_test.go\n945: \n946: ```go\n947: func TestLoadConfig_Defaults(t *testing.T) {\n948:     cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n949:     require.NoError(t, err)\n950:     \n951:     assert.True(t, cfg.LeaderElection)\n952:     assert.Equal(t, 10*time.Minute, cfg.SyncPeriod)\n953:     assert.Equal(t, 1, cfg.WorkerCount)\n954:     assert.Equal(t, 15*time.Minute, cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout)\n955: }\n956: \n957: func TestLoadConfig_FromEnv(t *testing.T) {\n958:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT\", \"30m\")\n959:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT\", \"5\")\n960:     t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION\", \"false\")\n961:     \n962:     cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n963:     require.NoError(t, err)\n964:     \n965:     assert.Equal(t, 30*time.Minute, cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout)\n966:     assert.Equal(t, 5, cfg.WorkerCount)\n967:     assert.False(t, cfg.LeaderElection)\n968: }\n969: \n970: func TestIdleTimeoutConfig_Validate(t *testing.T) {\n971:     // Valid config\n972:     validConfig := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n973:         DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n974:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n975:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n976:     }\n977:     require.NoError(t, validConfig.Validate())\n978:     \n979:     // Invalid: default < min\n980:     invalidConfig1 := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n981:         DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n982:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n983:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n984:     }\n985:     require.Error(t, invalidConfig1.Validate())\n986:     \n987:     // Invalid: default > max\n988:     invalidConfig2 := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n989:         DefaultTimeout: 48 * time.Hour,\n990:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n991:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n992:     }\n993:     require.Error(t, invalidConfig2.Validate())\n994: }\n995: ```\n996: \n997: ### Integration Tests\n998: \n999: ```go\n1000: func TestIntegration_Controller(t *testing.T) {\n1001:     if testing.Short() {\n1002:         t.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n1003:     }\n1004:     \n1005:     // Setup test environment\n1006:     cfg := &rest.Config{Host: os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\")}\n1007:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n1008:     require.NoError(t, runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme))\n1009:     \n1010:     // Create manager\n1011:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(cfg, ctrl.Options{\n1012:         Scheme: scheme,\n1013:     })\n1014:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1015:     \n1016:     // Setup reconciler\n1017:     reconciler := NewReconciler(mgr.GetClient(), mgr.GetScheme())\n1018:     require.NoError(t, reconciler.SetupWithManager(mgr))\n1019:     \n1020:     // Create test AgentRuntime\n1021:     ctx := context.Background()\n1022:     agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n1023:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n1024:             Name:      \"test-idle-cleanup\",\n1025:             Namespace: \"default\",\n1026:         },\n1027:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n1028:             Image:              \"test:latest\",\n1029:             IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](60), // 1 minute\n1030:         },\n1031:     }\n1032:     \n1033:     err = mgr.GetClient().Create(ctx, agentRuntime)\n1034:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1035:     \n1036:     // Update status with old last activity time\n1037:     agentRuntime.Status.LastActivityTime = &metav1.Time{\n1038:         Time: time.Now().Add(-2 * time.Minute), // 2 minutes ago\n1039:     }\n1040:     err = mgr.GetClient().Status().Update(ctx, agentRuntime)\n1041:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1042:     \n1043:     // Trigger reconciliation\n1044:     _, err = reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, reconcile.Request{\n1045:         NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test-idle-cleanup\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n1046:     })\n1047:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1048:     \n1049:     // Verify deletion\n1050:     err = mgr.GetClient().Get(ctx, types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test-idle-cleanup\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n1051:     require.Error(t, err)\n1052:     assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n1053: }\n1054: ```\n1055: \n1056: ### Test Execution\n1057: \n1058: ```bash\n1059: # Run all controller tests\n1060: make test PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n1061: \n1062: # Run with race detector\n1063: go test -race ./pkg/agentd/...\n1064: \n1065: # Run specific test categories\n1066: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestReconciler\"\n1067: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestCheckIdleTimeout\"\n1068: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestLoadConfig\"\n1069: \n1070: # With coverage\n1071: go test ./pkg/agentd/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n1072: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n1073: \n1074: # Integration tests (requires k8s cluster)\n1075: go test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -tags=integration\n1076: ```\n1077: \n1078: ---\n1079: \n1080: ## Security Considerations\n1081: \n1082: ### Resource Deletion\n1083: \n1084: - Deletion uses foreground propagation for graceful cleanup\n1085: - Only deletes resources in the same namespace the controller has access to\n1086: - RBAC rules must be carefully configured to allow only delete on AgentRuntime\n1087: - Audit logging should be enabled for deletion events\n1088: \n1089: ### RBAC Requirements\n1090: \n1091: ```yaml\n1092: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1093: kind: ClusterRole\n1094: metadata:\n1095:   name: agentd-idle-cleanup\n1096: rules:\n1097: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1098:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n1099:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n1100: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1101:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n1102:   verbs: [\"get\"]\n1103: ```\n1104: \n1105: ### Time Safety\n1106: \n1107: - Clock skew between controller and API server is handled via configurable tolerance\n1108: - Time comparisons use monotonic clocks where available\n1109: - Leap seconds are handled gracefully\n1110: \n1111: ### Logging Safety\n1112: \n1113: - Resource names and namespaces are logged at appropriate levels\n1114: - No sensitive data (tokens, credentials) is logged\n1115: - Log levels: DEBUG (V(2)) for timing details, INFO for deletions, WARN for errors\n1116: \n1117: ---\n1118: \n1119: ## Performance Considerations\n1120: \n1121: ### Scalability\n1122: \n1123: | Metric | Target | Notes |\n1124: |--------|--------|-------|\n1125: | Reconcile latency | < 100ms | P99 for single resource |\n1126: | Concurrent reconciles | 10+ | Configurable via worker count |\n1127: | Memory per resource | < 1KB | Minimal resource footprint |\n1128: | API calls per reconcile | 1-2 | Get + optional Delete |\n1129: \n1130: ### Optimization Strategies\n1131: \n1132: - Single API call per reconcile (Get only, Delete only when needed)\n1133: - Precise requeue timing based on remaining idle time\n1134: - No polling - event-driven reconciliation\n1135: - Minimal memory allocation in hot path\n1136: - Shared informer cache for reduced API server load\n1137: \n1138: ### Resource Usage\n1139: \n1140: - **Memory**: Scales with number of AgentRuntimes being watched\n1141: - **CPU**: Low baseline, spikes during bulk reconciliations\n1142: - **Network**: Minimal - only API calls for Get and Delete\n1143: - **Storage**: None (no persistent storage)\n1144: \n1145: ---\n1146: \n1147: ## Integration Points\n1148: \n1149: ### With AgentRuntime API\n1150: \n1151: ```go\n1152: // Watches AgentRuntime resources via controller-runtime\n1153: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n1154:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n1155:         For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n1156:         WithEventFilter(predicate.GenerationChangedPredicate{}).\n1157:         Complete(r)\n1158: }\n1159: ```\n1160: \n1161: ### With client-go\n1162: \n1163: ```go\n1164: // Uses generated client for typed operations\n1165: import runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n1166: \n1167: // Get AgentRuntime using controller-runtime client (wrapper around client-go)\n1168: err := r.client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime)\n1169: ```\n1170: \n1171: ### With Workload Manager\n1172: \n1173: The controller reads `LastActivityTime` which is updated by the workload manager:\n1174: \n1175: ```go\n1176: // LastActivityTime is set by workload manager when processing requests\n1177: lastActivity := agentRuntime.Status.LastActivityTime\n1178: ```\n1179: \n1180: ### With Metrics Server\n1181: \n1182: ```go\n1183: // Metrics are exposed for Prometheus scraping\n1184: metrics.Registry.MustRegister(reconciler.Metrics.ReconcileTotal)\n1185: metrics.Registry.MustRegister(reconciler.Metrics.CleanupTotal)\n1186: ```\n1187: \n1188: ---\n1189: \n1190: ## Dependencies\n1191: \n1192: ```go\n1193: import (\n1194:     \"context\"\n1195:     \"errors\"\n1196:     \"fmt\"\n1197:     \"os\"\n1198:     \"time\"\n1199:     \n1200:     \"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n1201:     corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n1202:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n1203:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n1204:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n1205:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n1206:     \"k8s.io/utils/ptr\"\n1207:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n1208:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log\"\n1209:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager\"\n1210:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile\"\n1211:     \n1212:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n1213: )\n1214: ```\n1215: \n1216: | Package | Purpose | Version |\n1217: |---------|---------|---------|\n1218: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller framework | v0.19.x |\n1219: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Metrics | v1.20.x |\n1220: | `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API types | v0.31.x |\n1221: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes utilities | v0.31.x |\n1222: | `k8s.io/utils` | Kubernetes helpers | v0.0.x |\n1223: \n1224: ---\n1225: \n1226: ## References\n1227: \n1228: - [AgentRuntime Types](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go) — AgentRuntime CRD types\n1229: - [client-go Spec](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md) — client-go library specification\n1230: - [Idle Cleanup (Sandbox)](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli-benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md) — Related sandbox idle cleanup design\n1231: - [controller-runtime](https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime) — Controller runtime documentation\n1232: - [Kubernetes Controllers](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/controller/) — Kubernetes controller patterns\n1233: \n1234: ---\n1235: \n1236: *AR-018 — Module: pkg/agentd — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 1236 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 Design: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018  \n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S (Small)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller is a Kubernetes controller that automatically deletes AgentRuntime resources that have exceeded their configured idle timeout. It monitors the `LastActivityTime` field in AgentRuntime status and compares it against the `IdleTimeoutSeconds` specified in the spec to determine when a resource should be cleaned up.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **AgentRuntime API (pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1)**: Watches AgentRuntime resources\n- **client-go library**: Uses generated Kubernetes clientset for API interactions\n- **controller-runtime**: Manages the controller lifecycle and reconciliation loop\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775885284375,"end":1775885284397}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885284405,"sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","part":{"id":"prt_d7b02e8310012dkY17wtq6fk1w","messageID":"msg_d7b02da5e001Lg1aGtsudcgFs7","sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 Design: CLI Binary Entry Points\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-019  \n6: **Module:** `cmd`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M (Medium)\n9: \n10: This module provides the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling.\n11: \n12: ### Components\n13: \n14: | Binary | Purpose | Package Dependency |\n15: |--------|---------|-------------------|\n16: | `agentd` | Idle cleanup controller for AgentRuntime resources | `pkg/agentd` |\n17: | `router` | HTTP session routing proxy with JWT authentication | `pkg/router` |\n18: | `workload-manager` | Sandbox orchestration controller with CRD management | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n19: | `picod` | Sandbox daemon for code execution inside sandbox pods | `pkg/picod` |\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Architecture\n24: \n25: ### High-Level Design\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                        AgentCube Platform                                    │\n30: │                                                                              │\n31: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐     │\n32: │  │   agentd     │  │    router    │  │workload-mgr  │  │    picod     │     │\n33: │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │  │  ┌────────┐  │     │\n34: │  │  │Reconciler│  │  │  │  Gin   │  │  │  │Controller│  │  │  │  HTTP  │  │     │\n35: │  │  │(controller│  │  │  │Server  │  │  │  │ + API    │  │  │  │ Server │  │     │\n36: │  │  │-runtime) │  │  │  │        │  │  │  │ Server   │  │  │  │        │  │     │\n37: │  │  └────┬───┘  │  │  └───┬────┘  │  │  └────┬───┘  │  │  └───┬────┘  │     │\n38: │  │       │      │  │      │       │  │       │      │  │      │       │     │\n39: │  │  K8s API    │  │  Redis/Valkey│  │  K8s API      │  │  Workspace    │     │\n40: │  │       │      │  │      │       │  │       │      │  │      │       │     │\n41: │  └───────┼──────┘  └──────┼───────┘  └───────┼──────┘  └──────┼───────┘     │\n42: │          │                │                  │                │             │\n43: │          └────────────────┴──────────────────┴────────────────┘             │\n44: │                                 │                                           │\n45: │                      Kubernetes Cluster + Redis/Valkey                     │\n46: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Component Interactions\n50: \n51: ```\n52: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n53: │                        Binary Startup & Integration                          │\n54: │                                                                              │\n55: │  ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐         │\n56: │  │   agentd/main   │    │  router/main    │    │ workload-mgr/main│         │\n57: │  │       │         │    │       │         │    │       │          │         │\n58: │  │       ▼         │    │       ▼         │    │       ▼          │         │\n59: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐     │         │\n60: │  │  │ flag    │    │    │  │ flag    │    │    │  │ flag    │     │         │\n61: │  │  │ parse   │    │    │  │ parse   │    │    │  │ parse   │     │         │\n62: │  │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘     │         │\n63: │  │       ▼         │    │       ▼         │    │       ▼          │         │\n64: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐     │         │\n65: │  │  │ K8s cfg │    │    │  │ Redis   │    │    │  │ K8s cfg │     │         │\n66: │  │  │ client  │    │    │  │ client  │    │    │  │ client  │     │         │\n67: │  │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘     │         │\n68: │  │       ▼         │    │       ▼         │    │       ▼          │         │\n69: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐     │         │\n70: │  │  │Manager  │    │    │  │ Gin     │    │    │  │Manager  │     │         │\n71: │  │  │(ctrl-runtime)│  │    │  │ Server  │    │    │  │(ctrl-runtime)│ │         │\n72: │  │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘     │         │\n73: │  │       ▼         │    │       ▼         │    │       ▼          │         │\n74: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐    │    │  ┌─────────┐     │         │\n75: │  │  │Reconciler│   │    │  │Router   │    │    │  │Controller│    │         │\n76: │  │  │(agentd) │    │    │  │Handlers │    │    │  │(workload)│    │         │\n77: │  │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘    │    │  └────┬────┘     │         │\n78: │  │       │         │    │       │         │    │       │          │         │\n79: │  │  client-go      │    │  store pkg      │    │  client-go       │         │\n80: │  │       │         │    │       │         │    │       │          │         │\n81: │  └───────┼─────────┘    └───────┼─────────┘    └───────┼──────────┘         │\n82: │          │                      │                      │                     │\n83: │          └──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘                     │\n84: │                                 │                                             │\n85: │                          ┌─────────────┐                                      │\n86: │                          │  K8s API    │                                      │\n87: │                          │  Server     │                                      │\n88: │                          └─────────────┘                                      │\n89: │                                                                              │\n90: │  ┌─────────────────┐                                                         │\n91: │  │   picod/main    │                                                         │\n92: │  │       │         │                                                         │\n93: │  │       ▼         │                                                         │\n94: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │                                                         │\n95: │  │  │ flag    │    │                                                         │\n96: │  │  │ parse   │    │                                                         │\n97: │  │  └────┬────┘    │                                                         │\n98: │  │       ▼         │                                                         │\n99: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │                                                         │\n100: │  │  │workspace│    │                                                         │\n101: │  │  │ init    │    │                                                         │\n102: │  │  └────┬────┘    │                                                         │\n103: │  │       ▼         │                                                         │\n104: │  │  ┌─────────┐    │                                                         │\n105: │  │  │ HTTP    │    │                                                         │\n106: │  │  │ Server  │    │                                                         │\n107: │  │  └────┬────┘    │                                                         │\n108: │  │       │         │                                                         │\n109: │  │  pkg/picod      │                                                         │\n110: │  └───────┼─────────┘                                                         │\n111: │          │                                                                   │\n112: │          ▼                                                                   │\n113: │    Sandbox Pod (isolated)                                                    │\n114: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Directory Structure\n120: \n121: ```\n122: cmd/\n123: ├── design.md                   # This file\n124: ├── agentd/\n125: │   └── main.go                 # Idle cleanup controller entry point (~80 lines)\n126: ├── router/\n127: │   └── main.go                 # Session routing proxy entry point (~100 lines)\n128: ├── workload-manager/\n129: │   └── main.go                 # Sandbox orchestration entry point (~120 lines)\n130: └── picod/\n131:     └── main.go                 # Sandbox daemon entry point (~90 lines)\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Data Structures\n137: \n138: ### Common Flag Types\n139: \n140: ```go\n141: // GracefulShutdownConfig holds graceful shutdown configuration.\n142: type GracefulShutdownConfig struct {\n143:     // Timeout is the maximum time to wait for graceful shutdown\n144:     Timeout time.Duration\n145:     // Signals lists the OS signals to handle for graceful shutdown\n146:     Signals []os.Signal\n147: }\n148: \n149: // DefaultGracefulShutdownConfig returns the default configuration.\n150: func DefaultGracefulShutdownConfig() GracefulShutdownConfig {\n151:     return GracefulShutdownConfig{\n152:         Timeout: 30 * time.Second,\n153:         Signals: []os.Signal{syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM},\n154:     }\n155: }\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ### agentd Configuration\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: // AgentdConfig holds the agentd binary configuration.\n162: type AgentdConfig struct {\n163:     // Kubeconfig is the path to kubeconfig file (empty = in-cluster)\n164:     Kubeconfig string\n165:     // SyncPeriod is the full sync period for all AgentRuntimes\n166:     SyncPeriod time.Duration\n167:     // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n168:     GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n169: }\n170: \n171: // DefaultAgentdConfig returns the default configuration.\n172: func DefaultAgentdConfig() AgentdConfig {\n173:     return AgentdConfig{\n174:         Kubeconfig:      \"\",\n175:         SyncPeriod:      5 * time.Minute,\n176:         GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n177:     }\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: ### router Configuration\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: // RouterConfig holds the router binary configuration.\n185: type RouterConfig struct {\n186:     // Port is the HTTP server port\n187:     Port int\n188:     // Debug enables debug logging\n189:     Debug bool\n190:     // RedisAddr is the Redis/Valkey server address\n191:     RedisAddr string\n192:     // WorkloadManagerURL is the workload manager service URL\n193:     WorkloadManagerURL string\n194:     // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n195:     GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n196: }\n197: \n198: // DefaultRouterConfig returns the default configuration.\n199: func DefaultRouterConfig() RouterConfig {\n200:     return RouterConfig{\n201:         Port:            8080,\n202:         Debug:           false,\n203:         GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n204:     }\n205: }\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ### workload-manager Configuration\n209: \n210: ```go\n211: // WorkloadManagerConfig holds the workload-manager binary configuration.\n212: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n213:     // Port is the HTTP API server port\n214:     Port int\n215:     // Kubeconfig is the path to kubeconfig file (empty = in-cluster)\n216:     Kubeconfig string\n217:     // RedisAddr is the Redis/Valkey server address\n218:     RedisAddr string\n219:     // DefaultImage is the default sandbox image\n220:     DefaultImage string\n221:     // Namespace is the default namespace for resources\n222:     Namespace string\n223:     // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n224:     GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n225: }\n226: \n227: // DefaultWorkloadManagerConfig returns the default configuration.\n228: func DefaultWorkloadManagerConfig() WorkloadManagerConfig {\n229:     return WorkloadManagerConfig{\n230:         Port:            8080,\n231:         DefaultImage:    \"ubuntu:22.04\",\n232:         Namespace:       \"default\",\n233:         GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n234:     }\n235: }\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### picod Configuration\n239: \n240: ```go\n241: // PicodConfig holds the picod binary configuration.\n242: type PicodConfig struct {\n243:     // Port is the HTTP server port\n244:     Port int\n245:     // Workspace is the workspace root directory\n246:     Workspace string\n247:     // ReadHeaderTimeout is the HTTP read header timeout\n248:     ReadHeaderTimeout time.Duration\n249: }\n250: \n251: // DefaultPicodConfig returns the default configuration.\n252: func DefaultPicodConfig() PicodConfig {\n253:     return PicodConfig{\n254:         Port:              8080,\n255:         Workspace:         \".\",\n256:         ReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n257:     }\n258: }\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## API Contracts\n264: \n265: ### Binary Entry Points\n266: \n267: Each binary follows the same basic structure:\n268: \n269: ```go\n270: func main() {\n271:     // 1. Parse flags\n272:     config := parseFlags()\n273:     \n274:     // 2. Validate configuration\n275:     if err := validateConfig(config); err != nil {\n276:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n277:         os.Exit(1)\n278:     }\n279:     \n280:     // 3. Log startup\n281:     logStartup(binaryName, version, config)\n282:     \n283:     // 4. Initialize dependencies\n284:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n285:     \n286:     // 5. Start service (blocking)\n287:     if err := run(ctx, config); err != nil {\n288:         fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n289:         os.Exit(3)\n290:     }\n291: }\n292: ```\n293: \n294: ### Service Startup Interface\n295: \n296: ```go\n297: // Runnable represents a service that can be started and stopped.\n298: type Runnable interface {\n299:     // Start begins the service and blocks until context cancellation or error.\n300:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n301:     // Stop initiates graceful shutdown with the given timeout.\n302:     Stop(timeout time.Duration) error\n303: }\n304: ```\n305: \n306: ### Flag Parsing Contract\n307: \n308: All binaries use the standard Go `flag` package:\n309: \n310: | Binary | Flag | Type | Default | Required | Description |\n311: |--------|------|------|---------|----------|-------------|\n312: | agentd | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | No | Path to kubeconfig |\n313: | agentd | `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | No | Full sync period |\n314: | agentd | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n315: | router | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP server port |\n316: | router | `--debug` | bool | false | No | Debug logging |\n317: | router | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Redis address |\n318: | router | `--workload-manager` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Workload manager URL |\n319: | router | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n320: | workload-manager | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP API port |\n321: | workload-manager | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | No | Path to kubeconfig |\n322: | workload-manager | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Redis address |\n323: | workload-manager | `--default-image` | string | ubuntu:22.04 | No | Default image |\n324: | workload-manager | `--namespace` | string | default | No | Default namespace |\n325: | workload-manager | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n326: | picod | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP server port |\n327: | picod | `--workspace` | string | . | No | Workspace directory |\n328: | picod | `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | No | Read header timeout |\n329: \n330: ### Kubernetes Client Integration\n331: \n332: Binaries that interact with Kubernetes use the client-go library defined in `deployment/client-go.md`:\n333: \n334: ```go\n335: // createK8sClient creates a Kubernetes client from configuration.\n336: func createK8sClient(kubeconfig string) (*kubernetes.Clientset, error) {\n337:     // Build config from kubeconfig or in-cluster\n338:     config, err := clientcmd.NewNonInteractiveDeferredLoadingClientConfig(\n339:         &clientcmd.ClientConfigLoadingRules{ExplicitPath: kubeconfig},\n340:         &clientcmd.ConfigOverrides{},\n341:     ).ClientConfig()\n342:     if err != nil {\n343:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load kubeconfig: %w\", err)\n344:     }\n345:     \n346:     // Create clientset\n347:     clientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n348:     if err != nil {\n349:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create clientset: %w\", err)\n350:     }\n351:     \n352:     return clientset, nil\n353: }\n354: ```\n355: \n356: ### controller-runtime Integration\n357: \n358: ```go\n359: // createManager creates a controller-runtime manager.\n360: func createManager(kubeconfig string, syncPeriod time.Duration) (ctrl.Manager, error) {\n361:     config, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n362:     if err != nil {\n363:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get config: %w\", err)\n364:     }\n365:     \n366:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(config, ctrl.Options{\n367:         Scheme:     scheme,\n368:         SyncPeriod: &syncPeriod,\n369:     })\n370:     if err != nil {\n371:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create manager: %w\", err)\n372:     }\n373:     \n374:     return mgr, nil\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ---\n379: \n380: ## Error Handling\n381: \n382: ### Error Types\n383: \n384: | Error | Code | Description | Binary |\n385: |-------|------|-------------|--------|\n386: | `FlagError` | 1 | Missing or invalid CLI flags | All |\n387: | `ConfigError` | 1 | Configuration loading failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n388: | `ConnectionError` | 2 | Redis/Valkey connection failure | router, workload-manager |\n389: | `SchemeError` | 2 | CRD scheme registration failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n390: | `ServerError` | 3 | HTTP server startup failure | router, workload-manager, picod |\n391: | `WorkspaceError` | 2 | Workspace initialization failure | picod |\n392: \n393: ### Exit Codes\n394: \n395: | Exit Code | Meaning |\n396: |-----------|---------|\n397: | 0 | Clean shutdown |\n398: | 1 | Configuration error |\n399: | 2 | Dependency initialization error |\n400: | 3 | Server startup error |\n401: | 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n402: | 143 | Terminated (SIGTERM) |\n403: \n404: ### Error Propagation\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: // FatalError represents an error that should cause immediate exit.\n408: type FatalError struct {\n409:     Code    int\n410:     Message string\n411:     Cause   error\n412: }\n413: \n414: func (e *FatalError) Error() string {\n415:     if e.Cause != nil {\n416:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", e.Message, e.Cause)\n417:     }\n418:     return e.Message\n419: }\n420: \n421: // Wrap wraps an error with a fatal error code.\n422: func Wrap(code int, message string, err error) *FatalError {\n423:     return &FatalError{Code: code, Message: message, Cause: err}\n424: }\n425: ```\n426: \n427: ---\n428: \n429: ## Testing Strategy\n430: \n431: ### Unit Testing\n432: \n433: ```go\n434: // Test flag parsing\n435: func TestParseFlags(t *testing.T) {\n436:     tests := []struct {\n437:         name     string\n438:         args     []string\n439:         expected Config\n440:         wantErr  bool\n441:     }{\n442:         {\n443:             name: \"default values\",\n444:             args: []string{\"cmd\"},\n445:             expected: Config{\n446:                 Port: 8080,\n447:                 // ...\n448:             },\n449:         },\n450:         // ...\n451:     }\n452:     // ...\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### Integration Testing\n457: \n458: | Test | Command | Expected |\n459: |------|---------|----------|\n460: | Build | `go build ./cmd/agentd/...` | Binary compiles |\n461: | Help | `./bin/agentd --help` | Usage printed, exit 0 |\n462: | Missing flags | `./bin/router` | Error printed, exit 1 |\n463: | Graceful shutdown | `timeout 2 ./bin/picod` | Exit 0 |\n464: \n465: ### Build Verification\n466: \n467: ```bash\n468: # Build all binaries\n469: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n470: go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router\n471: go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n472: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n473: \n474: # Verify binaries exist\n475: ls -la bin/\n476: ```\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ## Dependencies\n481: \n482: ### External Dependencies\n483: \n484: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n485: |---------|---------|---------|\n486: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.0 | Kubernetes controller framework |\n487: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes client library |\n488: | `k8s.io/api` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API types |\n489: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API machinery |\n490: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | latest | HTTP framework for router |\n491: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.7.3 | Redis client |\n492: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.0.56 | Valkey client |\n493: \n494: ### Internal Dependencies\n495: \n496: | Package | Purpose |\n497: |---------|---------|\n498: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd` | Idle cleanup reconciler |\n499: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Session routing handlers |\n500: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Sandbox orchestration |\n501: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Sandbox daemon |\n502: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | CRD types |\n503: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Redis/Valkey store |\n504: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated Kubernetes client |\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## Integration with client-go\n509: \n510: The binaries that interact with Kubernetes use the generated client-go library from `deployment/client-go.md`:\n511: \n512: ### Clientset Usage\n513: \n514: ```go\n515: import (\n516:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n517:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n518: )\n519: \n520: // Create clientset\n521: config, _ := ctrl.GetConfig()\n522: clientset, _ := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n523: \n524: // Access typed clients\n525: agentRuntimes := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace)\n526: codeInterpreters := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace)\n527: ```\n528: \n529: ### Informer Usage\n530: \n531: ```go\n532: import (\n533:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n534: )\n535: \n536: // Create informer factory\n537: factory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 5*time.Minute)\n538: \n539: // Get informers\n540: agentRuntimeInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()\n541: codeInterpreterInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters()\n542: ```\n543: \n544: ---\n545: \n546: ## Performance Characteristics\n547: \n548: | Binary | Memory (est.) | Startup Time | Notes |\n549: |--------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n550: | agentd | ~50MB | <5s | Reconciler only, no HTTP server |\n551: | router | ~30MB | <3s | Depends on Redis connection |\n552: | workload-manager | ~60MB | <5s | Controller + HTTP server |\n553: | picod | ~20MB | <2s | Lightweight daemon |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## Security Considerations\n558: \n559: ### RBAC Requirements\n560: \n561: #### agentd\n562: | Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n563: |----------|-----------|-------|\n564: | `agentruntimes` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` |\n565: | `agentruntimes/status` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `update`, `patch` |\n566: \n567: #### router\n568: | Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n569: |----------|-----------|-------|\n570: | `secrets` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n571: \n572: #### workload-manager\n573: | Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n574: |----------|-----------|-------|\n575: | `agentruntimes` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n576: | `codeinterpreters` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n577: | `codeinterpreters/status` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `update`, `patch` |\n578: | `pods` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n579: | `secrets` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n580: \n581: #### picod\n582: - Runs inside sandbox pod with container-local permissions\n583: - Workspace directory isolation\n584: - No Kubernetes API access required\n585: \n586: ### Sensitive Data Handling\n587: - Redis passwords via environment variables (not flags)\n588: - Kubernetes service account tokens (in-cluster) or kubeconfig files\n589: - No secrets logged at startup\n590: \n591: ---\n592: \n593: ## Build and Deployment\n594: \n595: ### Makefile Targets\n596: \n597: | Target | Description |\n598: |--------|-------------|\n599: | `build-agentd` | Build agentd binary |\n600: | `build-router` | Build router binary |\n601: | `build` | Build workload-manager binary (default) |\n602: | `build-all` | Build all binaries |\n603: | `run` | Run workload-manager locally |\n604: | `run-router` | Run router locally |\n605: | `docker-build` | Build workload-manager Docker image |\n606: | `docker-build-router` | Build router Docker image |\n607: | `docker-build-picod` | Build picod Docker image |\n608: \n609: ### Docker Images\n610: \n611: | Binary | Dockerfile | Image Name |\n612: |--------|------------|------------|\n613: | workload-manager | `docker/Dockerfile` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n614: | router | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n615: | picod | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | `picod:latest` |\n616: \n617: ---\n618: \n619: ## References\n620: \n621: - [client-go Library](../deployment/client-go.md) — Generated Kubernetes client\n622: - [Deployment Design](../deployment/design.md) — Helm charts and Dockerfiles\n623: - [project.md](../project.md) — Project context and architecture\n624: - [pkg/agentd](../pkg/agentd/) — Idle cleanup controller package\n625: - [pkg/router](../pkg/router/) — Session routing package\n626: - [pkg/workloadmanager](../pkg/workloadmanager/) — Sandbox orchestration package\n627: - [pkg/picod](../pkg/picod/) — Sandbox daemon package\n\n(End of file - total 627 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 Design: CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-019  \n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThis module provides the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling.\n\n### Components\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Package Dependency |\n|--------|---------|-------------------|\n| `agentd` | Idle cleanup controller for AgentRuntime resources | `pkg/agentd` |\n| `router` | HTTP session routing proxy with JWT authentication | `pkg/router` |\n| `workload-manager` | Sandbox orchestration controller with CRD management | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| `picod` 