{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885284419,"sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","part":{"id":"prt_d7b02efd1001QXMCT5QcQDTRO4","messageID":"msg_d7b02da5e001Lg1aGtsudcgFs7","sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** S  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n7: > **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: AR-014 implements a Valkey-backed storage provider for the Store interface defined in AR-012. Valkey is an open-source Redis fork that provides high-performance key-value storage with clustering support. This implementation uses the `valkey-go` client library.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-4.1 — Valkey Store Core Structure\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 4.1.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey.go` with `valkeyStore` struct | File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds | 0.5h |\n22: | 4.1.2 | Define `valkeyOptions` struct with `InitAddress []string`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient` | Struct fields align with valkey-go ClientOption | 0.5h |\n23: | 4.1.3 | Implement `newValkeyStore()` constructor | Returns Store interface implementation | 0.5h |\n24: | 4.1.4 | Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment parsing | `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | 0.5h |\n25: | 4.1.5 | Add `sessionKey()` helper method for key construction | Returns `session:{id}` format | 0.25h |\n26: \n27: **Deliverable:** Valkey store structure compiles with proper configuration.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## ST-4.2 — Valkey Core Store Methods\n32: \n33: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n34: |---|------|--------------|------|\n35: | 4.2.1 | Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` | Returns nil on \"PONG\" response; returns error on failure | 0.5h |\n36: | 4.2.2 | Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Returns `ErrNotFound` for missing keys; validates empty sessionID | 1h |\n37: | 4.2.3 | Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` | Uses `DoMulti` atomic operation: SET NX + ZADD expiry + ZADD last_activity | 1h |\n38: | 4.2.4 | Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` | Uses SET XX flag; returns error if key doesn't exist | 0.5h |\n39: | 4.2.5 | Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error` | Uses `DoMulti` atomic: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM last_activity | 0.5h |\n40: | 4.2.6 | Implement `Close() error` | Calls `s.cli.Close()`; returns nil | 0.25h |\n41: \n42: **Deliverable:** All core CRUD operations work with Valkey backend.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## ST-4.3 — Valkey Index Management Methods\n47: \n48: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n49: |---|------|--------------|------|\n50: | 4.3.1 | Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Uses `ZRANGEBYSCORE` on `session:expiry`; returns nil if limit <= 0 | 1h |\n51: | 4.3.2 | Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Uses `ZRANGEBYSCORE` on `session:last_activity` | 1h |\n52: | 4.3.3 | Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper | Uses `MGET` for batch fetch; skips orphaned entries gracefully | 1h |\n53: | 4.3.4 | Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` | Checks EXISTS first; uses `time.Now()` if at.IsZero() | 0.5h |\n54: \n55: **Deliverable:** Index operations support session lifecycle management.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## ST-4.4 — Valkey Error Handling\n60: \n61: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n62: |---|------|--------------|------|\n63: | 4.4.1 | Translate `valkey.IsValkeyNil()` to `ErrNotFound` | Unit test: missing key returns `ErrNotFound` | 0.5h |\n64: | 4.4.2 | Handle SET NX failure (session already exists) | Returns \"session already exists\" error | 0.5h |\n65: | 4.4.3 | Handle SET XX failure (key not exists) | Returns \"key not exists\" error | 0.5h |\n66: | 4.4.4 | Handle `DoMulti` partial failures | Returns error from first failed command | 0.5h |\n67: \n68: **Deliverable:** Error handling consistent with Redis implementation.\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## ST-4.5 — Unit Tests — Valkey Implementation\n73: \n74: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n75: |---|------|--------------|------|\n76: | 4.5.1 | Write `TestValkeyStore_Ping` — success and failure | Mock valkey-go client; verify \"PONG\" parsing | 1h |\n77: | 4.5.2 | Write `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID` — validation, not found, success | Verify `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` translation | 1h |\n78: | 4.5.3 | Write `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox` — validation (nil, empty ID, zero ExpiresAt), success, duplicate | Verify atomic `DoMulti` with SET NX + ZADD x2 | 1.5h |\n79: | 4.5.4 | Write `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox` — validation, missing key, success | Verify SET XX behavior | 1h |\n80: | 4.5.5 | Write `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` — validation, success, idempotent | Verify atomic cleanup of session + indexes | 1h |\n81: | 4.5.6 | Write `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` — limit <= 0, expired sessions, limit applied | Verify `ZRANGEBYSCORE` + `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` | 1h |\n82: | 4.5.7 | Write `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` — inactive sessions | Similar to expired tests | 1h |\n83: | 4.5.8 | Write `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity` — validation, not found, zero time, specific time | Verify EXISTS check + ZADD | 1h |\n84: | 4.5.9 | Write `TestValkeyStore_LoadSandboxesBySessionIDs` — empty, orphaned entries, batch load | Verify MGET + orphan skipping | 1h |\n85: | 4.5.10 | Write `TestValkeyStore_Close` — connection release | Verify `cli.Close()` called | 0.5h |\n86: \n87: **Deliverable:** `go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey` passes with >80% coverage.\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## ST-4.6 — Unit Tests — Configuration\n92: \n93: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n94: |---|------|--------------|------|\n95: | 4.6.1 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MissingAddr` — error when VALKEY_ADDR unset | Returns error | 0.5h |\n96: | 4.6.2 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordRequired` — error when password required but missing | Returns error | 0.5h |\n97: | 4.6.3 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordOptional` — success when VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false | Allows empty password | 0.5h |\n98: | 4.6.4 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MultipleAddresses` — comma-separated VALKEY_ADDR parsing | Splits and trims addresses | 0.5h |\n99: | 4.6.5 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_DisableCache` — parse VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE | Sets DisableCache field | 0.5h |\n100: | 4.6.6 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_ForceSingle` — parse VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE | Sets ForceSingleClient field | 0.5h |\n101: | 4.6.7 | Write `TestNewValkeyStore` — integration with makeValkeyOptions | Returns valid Store interface | 0.5h |\n102: \n103: **Deliverable:** Configuration tests pass with environment variable isolation.\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## ST-4.7 — Integration Tests\n108: \n109: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n110: |---|------|--------------|------|\n111: | 4.7.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` with testcontainers | Setup real Valkey container | 1.5h |\n112: | 4.7.2 | Write end-to-end CRUD test — full lifecycle | Store → Get → Update → Delete | 1h |\n113: | 4.7.3 | Write index consistency test | Verify ZSETs maintained correctly | 1h |\n114: | 4.7.4 | Write concurrent access safety test | 10 concurrent operations, no race | 1h |\n115: | 4.7.5 | Write orphaned entry tolerance test | Delete session data, verify list skips gracefully | 1h |\n116: \n117: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance.\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## ST-4.8 — Documentation\n122: \n123: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n124: |---|------|--------------|------|\n125: | 4.8.1 | Add package-level GoDoc for valkey.go | `go doc ./pkg/store` shows Valkey implementation | 0.5h |\n126: | 4.8.2 | Document `valkeyStore` struct with inline comments | Clear explanation of fields | 0.5h |\n127: | 4.8.3 | Document each method with purpose and behavior | Godoc format comments | 0.5h |\n128: | 4.8.4 | Add environment variable documentation | List all VALKEY_* variables | 0.5h |\n129: \n130: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for future maintainers.\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## Summary\n135: \n136: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n137: |-------|-------|------------|\n138: | ST-4.1: Core Structure | 5 | 2.25h |\n139: | ST-4.2: Core Methods | 6 | 3.75h |\n140: | ST-4.3: Index Management | 4 | 3h |\n141: | ST-4.4: Error Handling | 4 | 2h |\n142: | ST-4.5: Unit Tests (Valkey) | 10 | 10h |\n143: | ST-4.6: Unit Tests (Config) | 7 | 3.5h |\n144: | ST-4.7: Integration Tests | 5 | 5.5h |\n145: | ST-4.8: Documentation | 4 | 2h |\n146: | **Total** | **45** | **32h** |\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n151: \n152: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey.go` — Valkey Store implementation\n153: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` — Valkey unit tests\n154: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` — Valkey integration tests\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## Verification Commands\n159: \n160: ```bash\n161: # Build verification\n162: go build ./pkg/store/...\n163: \n164: # Unit test verification (all store tests)\n165: go test ./pkg/store/... -v\n166: \n167: # Valkey-specific tests\n168: go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey -v\n169: \n170: # Configuration tests\n171: go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestMakeValkey -v\n172: \n173: # Race detection\n174: go test ./pkg/store/... -race\n175: \n176: # Coverage report\n177: go test ./pkg/store/... -cover\n178: \n179: # Integration tests (requires Docker)\n180: go test ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -v\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Definition of Done\n186: \n187: - [ ] All 45 tasks complete\n188: - [ ] `valkeyStore` implements full `Store` interface\n189: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for valkey.go)\n190: - [ ] Configuration tests pass\n191: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey\n192: - [ ] Race detector clean\n193: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds\n194: - [ ] Documentation complete with GoDoc\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## Dependencies\n199: \n200: - AR-012: Store interface definition (`pkg/store/store.go`)\n201: - AR-013: Redis implementation (reference patterns)\n202: - `pkg/common/types` for `SandboxInfo` type\n203: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` v1.0.56\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## Design Notes\n208: \n209: - **Key naming:** Uses `session:{id}` prefix consistently\n210: - **Index keys:** `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity` (sorted sets)\n211: - **Atomic operations:** Uses `DoMulti` for multi-command atomicity\n212: - **Orphan tolerance:** List operations skip missing keys without failing\n213: - **Error translation:** `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound`\n214: - **Configuration:** Follows same pattern as Redis with VALKEY_* env vars\n\n(End of file - total 214 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** S  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-014 implements a Valkey-backed storage provider