n-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 10: Implement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI. This command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths.\n  Line 18: The system SHALL provide a `pack` command with well-defined options and sensible defaults.\n  Line 20: #### Scenario: Default options when pack runs without arguments\n  Line 21: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack` without specifying any options\n  Line 35: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /path/to/agent`\n  Line 40: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --agent-name my-custom-agent`\n  Line 42: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `agent_name=\"my-custom-agent\"` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n  Line 45: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --language java`\n  Line 47: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `language=\"java\"` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n  Line 50: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --port 9090`\n  Line 52: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `port=9090` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n  Line 61: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /nonexistent/path`\n  Line 64: - **AND** the CLI SHALL print \"Error packaging agent: {message}\" in red\n  Line 68: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /path/to/file.txt` where `file.txt` exists but is not a directory\n  Line 151: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` is called\n  Line 230: The system SHALL process language-specific dependencies as part of the pack operation.\n  Line 278: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime.pack` runs\n  Line 286: The system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n  Line 295: - **GIVEN** `output` option is `/tmp/packed-agent`\n  Line 298: - **AND** return `Path(\"/tmp/packed-agent\")`\n  Line 307: ### Requirement: Successful pack operation\n  Line 309: The system SHALL execute a complete pack workflow and report success.\n  Line 311: #### Scenario: Complete pack workflow\n  Line 315: - **WHEN** `pack` command completes successfully\n  Line 318:   2. Call `PackRuntime.pack()` with appropriate options\n  Line 332: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --verbose`\n  Line 345: The system SHALL handle pack errors gracefully with appropriate error messages.\n  Line 348: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception (e.g., `ValueError(\"Invalid workspace\")`)\n  Line 350: - **WHEN** the pack command catches the exception\n  Line 351: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL be called with `(e, \"packing agent\", verbose=False)`\n  Line 352: - **AND** the CLI SHALL print `\"Error packaging agent: Invalid workspace\"` in red\n  Line 357: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception (e.g., `RuntimeError(\"Docker not available\")`)\n  Line 359: - **WHEN** the pack command catches the exception\n  Line 360: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL be called with `(e, \"packing agent\", verbose=True)`\n  Line 361: - **AND** the CLI SHALL print `\"Error packaging agent: Docker not available\"` in red\n  Line 372: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --verbose`\n  Line 373: - **WHEN** the pack command handler executes\n  Line 378: - **WHEN** the pack command handler executes\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 347 matches (247 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":347,"truncated":true},"title":"pack","time":{"start":1775885293366,"end":1775885293375}}}}
