{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885298736,"sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0322aa001sBGHqqIYp24eQW","messageID":"msg_d7b031770001R1UEQ2DXbNd1d4","sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020 Design: CLI pack 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-020  \n6: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M (Medium)\n9: \n10: The `pack` command is the foundation of the AgentCube CLI toolchain. It validates agent workspace structure, processes metadata, handles dependencies, and optionally generates Dockerfiles to prepare agents for building and publishing. This command is the entry point for the agent lifecycle management workflow.\n11: \n12: ## Architecture\n13: \n14: ### High-Level Design\n15: \n16: ```\n17: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n18: │                           Agent Workspace                                    │\n19: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n20: │  │  Source Files    Metadata    Dependencies    Dockerfile (optional)     │  │\n21: │  │  (*.py/*.java)   (YAML)      (requirements/  (generated)               │  │\n22: │  │                              pom.xml)                                  │  │\n23: │  └────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n24: └───────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n25:                                     │\n26:                                     ▼\n27: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n28: │                              Pack Command                                    │\n29: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n30: │  │  1. Validate Workspace Structure                                       │  │\n31: │  │     ├── Check path exists and is directory                             │  │\n32: │  │     ├── Validate language-specific files                               │  │\n33: │  │     └── Verify entrypoint detection                                    │  │\n34: │  │                                                                        │  │\n35: │  │  2. Load/Create Metadata                                               │  │\n36: │  │     ├── Try agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml          │  │\n37: │  │     ├── Apply CLI option overrides                                     │  │\n38: │  │     └── Validate with Pydantic (AgentMetadata)                         │  │\n39: │  │                                                                        │  │\n40: │  │  3. Process Dependencies                                               │  │\n41: │  │     ├── Python: requirements.txt analysis                              │  │\n42: │  │     └── Java: pom.xml parsing                                          │  │\n43: │  │                                                                        │  │\n44: │  │  4. Generate Dockerfile (optional)                                     │  │\n45: │  │     ├── Language-specific template selection                         │  │\n46: │  │     └── Write to workspace root                                        │  │\n47: │  │                                                                        │  │\n48: │  │  5. Update Metadata & Report                                           │  │\n49: │  │     ├── Persist updated metadata                                       │  │\n50: │  │     └── Display success with paths                                     │  │\n51: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n52: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ### Component Architecture\n56: \n57: ```\n58: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n59: │                           PackRuntime Flow                                   │\n60: │                                                                              │\n61: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n62: │  │  CLI     │──►│  Pack    │──►│ Validate │──►│  Load    │──►│  Apply   │  │\n63: │  │  Options │   │  Runtime │   │ Workspace│   │ Metadata │   │ Overrides│  │\n64: │  └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n65: │                      │                                            │        │\n66: │                      ▼                                            ▼        │\n67: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n68: │  │  Report  │◀──│  Update  │◀──│ Generate │◀──│ Process  │◀──│ Validate │  │\n69: │  │  Result  │   │  Metadata│   │ Dockerfile│   │   Deps   │   │ Language │  │\n70: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n71: │                                                                              │\n72: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n73: ```\n74: \n75: ## Package Layout\n76: \n77: | Path | Role |\n78: |------|------|\n79: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n80: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n81: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n82: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, `pack` command, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n83: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n84: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n85: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` class implementation |\n86: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n87: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata` model, `MetadataService` |\n88: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring |\n89: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example Python agent |\n90: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example Java agent |\n91: \n92: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):\n93: - `agentcube`\n94: - `agentcube.cli`\n95: - `agentcube.runtime`\n96: - `agentcube.operations`\n97: - `agentcube.services`\n98: \n99: ## Console Script Entry Point\n100: \n101: ```toml\n102: [project.scripts]\n103: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n104: ```\n105: \n106: Typer app object:\n107: ```python\n108: app = typer.Typer(\n109:     name=\"agentcube\",\n110:     help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\",\n111:     no_args_is_help=True,\n112:     rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n113:     add_completion=False\n114: )\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ## Typer — Root Callback\n118: \n119: ```python\n120: def main(\n121:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n122:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n123:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n124:     ),\n125:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n126: ) -> None:\n127:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n128: ```\n129: \n130: Global verbose behavior:\n131: - When `verbose=True`, calls `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n132: \n133: ## Typer — `pack` Command\n134: \n135: ```python\n136: def pack(\n137:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n138:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n139:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n140:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n141:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n142:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n143:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n144:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n145:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n146: ) -> None:\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### Command Behavior\n150: \n151: 1. **Options and Defaults**:\n152:    - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\n153:    - `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`)\n154:    - `language` = `None` (`--language`)\n155:    - `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`)\n156:    - `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`)\n157:    - `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`)\n158:    - `description` = `None` (`--description`)\n159:    - `output` = `None` (`--output`)\n160:    - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n161: \n162: 2. **Successful Pack**:\n163:    - Uses Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n164:    - Prints success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path`\n165:    - Metadata path reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n166: \n167: 3. **Pack Failure Handling**:\n168:    - Calls `_handle_error(e, \"packing agent\", verbose)`\n169:    - Prints `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n170:    - If `verbose=True`, prints full traceback\n171:    - Exits with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n172: \n173: ## Helper Functions\n174: \n175: ### `version_callback`\n176: \n177: ```python\n178: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n179:     \"\"\"Display version and exit.\"\"\"\n180:     if value:\n181:         console.print(f\"AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}\")\n182:         raise typer.Exit()\n183: ```\n184: \n185: ### `_handle_error`\n186: \n187: ```python\n188: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n189:     \"\"\"Handle command errors with optional traceback.\"\"\"\n190:     console.print(f\"Error {command_name}: {e}\", style=\"red\")\n191:     if verbose:\n192:         console.print_exception()\n193:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ## Runtime Classes\n197: \n198: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n199: \n200: Core class responsible for packaging agent workspaces.\n201: \n202: ```python\n203: class PackRuntime:\n204:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n205:         \"\"\"Initialize PackRuntime with optional verbose logging.\"\"\"\n206:         self.verbose = verbose\n207:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n208:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n209: \n210:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n211:         \"\"\"\n212:         Main entry point for packaging an agent workspace.\n213:         \n214:         Args:\n215:             workspace_path: Path to the agent workspace directory\n216:             **options: CLI options and overrides\n217:             \n218:         Returns:\n219:             Dict containing packaging results including agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path\n220:         \"\"\"\n221:         ...\n222: ```\n223: \n224: #### Core Methods\n225: \n226: ##### `_validate_workspace_structure`\n227: \n228: ```python\n229: def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n230:     \"\"\"\n231:     Validate that workspace exists and contains required files.\n232:     \n233:     Raises:\n234:         ValueError: If workspace doesn't exist or is not a directory\n235:     \"\"\"\n236:     if not workspace_path.exists():\n237:         raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n238:     if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n239:         raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ##### `_load_or_create_metadata`\n243: \n244: ```python\n245: def _load_or_create_metadata(\n246:     self, \n247:     workspace_path: Path, \n248:     options: Dict[str, Any]\n249: ) -> AgentMetadata:\n250:     \"\"\"\n251:     Load existing metadata or create new from options.\n252:     \n253:     Metadata loading precedence:\n254:     1. agent_metadata.yaml (primary)\n255:     2. agent.yaml (fallback)\n256:     3. metadata.yaml (fallback)\n257:     4. Create new from defaults + options\n258:     \"\"\"\n259:     ...\n260: ```\n261: \n262: ##### `_apply_option_overrides`\n263: \n264: ```python\n265: def _apply_option_overrides(\n266:     self, \n267:     metadata: AgentMetadata, \n268:     options: Dict[str, Any]\n269: ) -> AgentMetadata:\n270:     \"\"\"\n271:     Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\n272:     \n273:     Override precedence (highest first):\n274:     1. Explicit CLI options\n275:     2. Existing metadata values\n276:     3. Default values from AgentMetadata\n277:     \"\"\"\n278:     ...\n279: ```\n280: \n281: ##### `_validate_language_compatibility`\n282: \n283: ```python\n284: def _validate_language_compatibility(\n285:     self, \n286:     workspace_path: Path, \n287:     metadata: AgentMetadata\n288: ) -> None:\n289:     \"\"\"\n290:     Validate workspace contents match declared language.\n291:     \n292:     Raises:\n293:         ValueError: If language-specific files are missing\n294:     \"\"\"\n295:     if metadata.language == \"python\":\n296:         self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n297:     elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n298:         self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n299: ```\n300: \n301: ##### `_validate_python_compatibility`\n302: \n303: ```python\n304: def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n305:     \"\"\"\n306:     Validate Python workspace has at least one .py file.\n307:     \n308:     Raises:\n309:         ValueError: If no Python files found\n310:     \"\"\"\n311:     py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n312:     if not py_files:\n313:         raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ##### `_validate_java_compatibility`\n317: \n318: ```python\n319: def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n320:     \"\"\"\n321:     Validate Java workspace has pom.xml.\n322:     \n323:     Raises:\n324:         ValueError: If pom.xml not found\n325:     \"\"\"\n326:     pom_path = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n327:     if not pom_path.exists():\n328:         raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace (required for Java agents)\")\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ##### `_process_dependencies`\n332: \n333: ```python\n334: def _process_dependencies(\n335:     self, \n336:     workspace_path: Path, \n337:     metadata: AgentMetadata\n338: ) -> None:\n339:     \"\"\"\n340:     Process and validate language-specific dependencies.\n341:     \"\"\"\n342:     if metadata.language == \"python\":\n343:         self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n344:     elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n345:         self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n346: ```\n347: \n348: ##### `_process_python_dependencies`\n349: \n350: ```python\n351: def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n352:     \"\"\"\n353:     Process Python requirements.txt if present.\n354:     Validates file exists and logs dependency count.\n355:     \"\"\"\n356:     req_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n357:     if req_file.exists():\n358:         deps = [line.strip() for line in req_file.read_text().splitlines() \n359:                 if line.strip() and not line.startswith(\"#\")]\n360:         self.logger.info(f\"Found {len(deps)} Python dependencies\")\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ##### `_process_java_dependencies`\n364: \n365: ```python\n366: def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n367:     \"\"\"\n368:     Process Java Maven dependencies from pom.xml.\n369:     \"\"\"\n370:     import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n371:     \n372:     pom_path = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n373:     if pom_path.exists():\n374:         try:\n375:             tree = ET.parse(pom_path)\n376:             root = tree.getroot()\n377:             # Count dependency elements\n378:             deps = root.findall(\".//{http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0}dependency\")\n379:             self.logger.info(f\"Found {len(deps)} Maven dependencies\")\n380:         except ET.ParseError as e:\n381:             self.logger.warning(f\"Could not parse pom.xml: {e}\")\n382: ```\n383: \n384: ##### `_generate_dockerfile`\n385: \n386: ```python\n387: def _generate_dockerfile(\n388:     self, \n389:     workspace_path: Path, \n390:     metadata: AgentMetadata\n391: ) -> Optional[Path]:\n392:     \"\"\"\n393:     Generate Dockerfile based on language and metadata.\n394:     \n395:     Args:\n396:         workspace_path: Path to agent workspace\n397:         metadata: Agent metadata with configuration\n398:         \n399:     Returns:\n400:         Path to generated Dockerfile, or None if generation skipped\n401:     \"\"\"\n402:     dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n403:     \n404:     if metadata.language == \"python\":\n405:         content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n406:     elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n407:         content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n408:     else:\n409:         self.logger.warning(f\"Unsupported language for Dockerfile generation: {metadata.language}\")\n410:         return None\n411:     \n412:     dockerfile_path.write_text(content)\n413:     self.logger.info(f\"Generated Dockerfile at {dockerfile_path}\")\n414:     return dockerfile_path\n415: ```\n416: \n417: ##### `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n418: \n419: ```python\n420: def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n421:     \"\"\"\n422:     Generate Python-specific Dockerfile content.\n423:     \n424:     Template includes:\n425:     - Python 3.11 slim base image\n426:     - Working directory setup\n427:     - Requirements installation\n428:     - Source code copying\n429:     - Entrypoint configuration\n430:     - Port exposure\n431:     \"\"\"\n432:     entrypoint = metadata.entrypoint or \"python main.py\"\n433:     port = metadata.port or 8080\n434:     \n435:     return f'''FROM python:3.11-slim\n436: \n437: WORKDIR /app\n438: \n439: # Install dependencies\n440: COPY requirements.txt .\n441: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n442: \n443: # Copy source code\n444: COPY . .\n445: \n446: # Expose port\n447: EXPOSE {port}\n448: \n449: # Run the agent\n450: CMD [\"{entrypoint}\"]\n451: '''\n452: ```\n453: \n454: ##### `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n455: \n456: ```python\n457: def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n458:     \"\"\"\n459:     Generate Java-specific Dockerfile content.\n460:     \n461:     Template includes:\n462:     - Maven build stage\n463:     - JAR extraction\n464:     - Runtime stage with minimal base\n465:     - Port exposure\n466:     \"\"\"\n467:     port = metadata.port or 8080\n468:     \n469:     return f'''# Build stage\n470: FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17-alpine AS builder\n471: \n472: WORKDIR /app\n473: COPY pom.xml .\n474: COPY src ./src\n475: \n476: RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n477: \n478: # Runtime stage\n479: FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\n480: \n481: WORKDIR /app\n482: \n483: # Copy built JAR\n484: COPY --from=builder /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n485: \n486: # Expose port\n487: EXPOSE {port}\n488: \n489: # Run the agent\n490: ENTRYPOINT [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"app.jar\"]\n491: '''\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ##### `_update_pack_metadata`\n495: \n496: ```python\n497: def _update_pack_metadata(\n498:     self, \n499:     workspace_path: Path, \n500:     metadata: AgentMetadata, \n501:     dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]\n502: ) -> None:\n503:     \"\"\"\n504:     Update metadata with pack results.\n505:     \n506:     Sets:\n507:     - pack_timestamp: Current UTC time\n508:     - dockerfile_generated: Whether Dockerfile was created\n509:     \"\"\"\n510:     from datetime import datetime, timezone\n511:     \n512:     metadata.pack_timestamp = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n513:     metadata.dockerfile_generated = dockerfile_path is not None\n514:     \n515:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n516: ```\n517: \n518: ##### `_prepare_output_path`\n519: \n520: ```python\n521: def _prepare_output_path(\n522:     self, \n523:     workspace_path: Path, \n524:     output_path: Optional[str]\n525: ) -> Path:\n526:     \"\"\"\n527:     Resolve output path for packaged workspace.\n528:     \n529:     Args:\n530:         workspace_path: Source workspace path\n531:         output_path: Optional explicit output path\n532:         \n533:     Returns:\n534:         Resolved output path\n535:     \"\"\"\n536:     if output_path:\n537:         return Path(output_path)\n538:     return workspace_path\n539: ```\n540: \n541: ##### `_infer_entrypoint`\n542: \n543: ```python\n544: def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n545:     \"\"\"\n546:     Attempt to infer entrypoint from workspace contents.\n547:     \n548:     Args:\n549:         workspace_path: Path to workspace\n550:         language: Programming language\n551:         \n552:     Returns:\n553:         Inferred entrypoint command\n554:     \"\"\"\n555:     if language == \"python\":\n556:         # Look for main.py, app.py, or any .py file\n557:         for candidate in [\"main.py\", \"app.py\", \"agent.py\"]:\n558:             if (workspace_path / candidate).exists():\n559:                 return f\"python {candidate}\"\n560:         # Fallback to first .py file\n561:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n562:         if py_files:\n563:             return f\"python {py_files[0].name}\"\n564:         return \"python main.py\"\n565:     \n566:     elif language == \"java\":\n567:         # For Java, entrypoint is typically the JAR\n568:         return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n569:     \n570:     return \"\"\n571: ```\n572: \n573: ## Service Classes\n574: \n575: ### `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n576: \n577: Service for loading, saving, and validating agent metadata.\n578: \n579: ```python\n580: class MetadataService:\n581:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n582:         self.verbose = verbose\n583:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n584: \n585:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n586:         \"\"\"\n587:         Load metadata from workspace.\n588:         \n589:         Loading precedence:\n590:         1. agent_metadata.yaml\n591:         2. agent.yaml\n592:         3. metadata.yaml\n593:         \n594:         Raises:\n595:             FileNotFoundError: If no metadata file exists\n596:         \"\"\"\n597:         for filename in [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]:\n598:             filepath = workspace_path / filename\n599:             if filepath.exists():\n600:                 data = yaml.safe_load(filepath.read_text())\n601:                 return AgentMetadata.model_validate(data)\n602:         \n603:         raise FileNotFoundError(f\"No metadata file found in {workspace_path}\")\n604: \n605:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n606:         \"\"\"\n607:         Save metadata to workspace.\n608:         \n609:         Always writes to agent_metadata.yaml with:\n610:         - default_flow_style=False\n611:         - indent=2\n612:         - sort_keys=False\n613:         - exclude_none=True\n614:         \"\"\"\n615:         filepath = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n616:         data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n617:         yaml.dump(data, filepath.open(\"w\"), \n618:                   default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)\n619: \n620:     def update_metadata(\n621:         self, \n622:         workspace_path: Path, \n623:         updates: Dict[str, Any]\n624:     ) -> AgentMetadata:\n625:         \"\"\"Load, update, and save metadata.\"\"\"\n626:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n627:         for key, value in updates.items():\n628:             setattr(metadata, key, value)\n629:         self.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n630:         return metadata\n631: \n632:     def validate_workspace(\n633:         self, \n634:         workspace_path: Path, \n635:         metadata: AgentMetadata\n636:     ) -> bool:\n637:         \"\"\"Validate workspace contents match metadata.\"\"\"\n638:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n639:             self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n640:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n641:             self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n642:         return True\n643: \n644:     def _validate_python_workspace(\n645:         self, \n646:         workspace_path: Path, \n647:         metadata: AgentMetadata\n648:     ) -> None:\n649:         \"\"\"Python-specific validation.\"\"\"\n650:         if not list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\")):\n651:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n652: \n653:     def _validate_java_workspace(\n654:         self, \n655:         workspace_path: Path, \n656:         metadata: AgentMetadata\n657:     ) -> None:\n658:         \"\"\"Java-specific validation.\"\"\"\n659:         if not (workspace_path / \"pom.xml\").exists():\n660:             raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")\n661: ```\n662: \n663: ## Data Models\n664: \n665: ### `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n666: \n667: Core metadata model for agent configuration.\n668: \n669: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n670: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n671: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n672: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n673: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n674: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n675: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n676: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n677: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n678: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n679: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n680: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n681: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n682: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n683: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n684: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n685: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n686: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n687: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n688: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n689: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n690: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n691: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n692: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n693: | `pack_timestamp` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | ISO timestamp of pack operation |\n694: | `dockerfile_generated` | `Optional[bool]` | `None` | Whether Dockerfile was generated |\n695: \n696: #### Validators\n697: \n698: ```python\n699: @field_validator(\"language\")\n700: @classmethod\n701: def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n702:     \"\"\"Validate and normalize language.\"\"\"\n703:     v = v.lower()\n704:     if v not in (\"python\", \"java\"):\n705:         raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n706:     return v\n707: \n708: @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n709: @classmethod\n710: def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n711:     \"\"\"Validate and normalize build_mode.\"\"\"\n712:     v = v.lower()\n713:     if v not in (\"local\", \"cloud\"):\n714:         raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n715:     return v\n716: \n717: @field_validator(\"port\")\n718: @classmethod\n719: def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n720:     \"\"\"Validate port number.\"\"\"\n721:     if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n722:         raise ValueError(f\"Invalid port: {v}. Must be between 1 and 65535\")\n723:     return v\n724: ```\n725: \n726: ### `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n727: \n728: Dataclass for CLI option packaging.\n729: \n730: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n731: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n732: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override agent name |\n733: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` | Language override |\n734: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Entrypoint override |\n735: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | Port override |\n736: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` | Build mode override |\n737: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Requirements file path |\n738: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Description override |\n739: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Workload manager URL |\n740: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Router URL |\n741: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Readiness probe path |\n742: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | Readiness probe port |\n743: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL |\n744: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n745: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n746: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Agent endpoint |\n747: \n748: ```python\n749: @dataclass\n750: class MetadataOptions:\n751:     \"\"\"Options for metadata creation/overrides during pack.\"\"\"\n752:     \n753:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n754:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n755:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n756:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n757:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n758:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n759:     description: Optional[str] = None\n760:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n761:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n762:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n763:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n764:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n765:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n766:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n767:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n768:     \n769:     @classmethod\n770:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n771:         \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from dict, filtering None values.\"\"\"\n772:         filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if v is not None}\n773:         return cls(**filtered)\n774: ```\n775: \n776: ## Dependencies\n777: \n778: ### Required Dependencies (`pyproject.toml`)\n779: \n780: ```toml\n781: [project]\n782: dependencies = [\n783:     \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n784:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n785:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n786:     \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n787:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n788:     \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n789:     \"packaging>=23.0\",\n790:     \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n791:     \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n792: ]\n793: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n794: ```\n795: \n796: ### Optional Dependencies\n797: \n798: ```toml\n799: [project.optional-dependencies]\n800: k8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n801: dev = [\n802:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n803:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n804:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n805:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n806:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n807:     \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n808:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n809: ]\n810: test = [\n811:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n812:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n813:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n814:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n815:     \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n816: ]\n817: ```\n818: \n819: ## Module Exports\n820: \n821: ### `agentcube/__init__.py`\n822: \n823: ```python\n824: \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n825: \n826: __version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n827: __author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"\n828: __email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"\n829: \n830: from agentcube.cli.main import app\n831: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n832: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n833: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n834: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n835: \n836: __all__ = [\n837:     \"app\",\n838:     \"PackRuntime\",\n839:     \"BuildRuntime\", \n840:     \"PublishRuntime\",\n841:     \"InvokeRuntime\",\n842: ]\n843: ```\n844: \n845: ### `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n846: \n847: ```python\n848: \"\"\"Runtime modules for agent lifecycle operations.\"\"\"\n849: \n850: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n851: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n852: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n853: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n854: from agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\n855: from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n856: \n857: __all__ = [\n858:     \"PackRuntime\",\n859:     \"BuildRuntime\",\n860:     \"PublishRuntime\",\n861:     \"InvokeRuntime\",\n862:     \"StatusRuntime\",\n863:     \"MetadataOptions\",\n864: ]\n865: ```\n866: \n867: ## Workflow Diagram\n868: \n869: ```\n870: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n871: │                        Pack Command Execution Flow                           │\n872: │                                                                              │\n873: │  User Input                                                                  │\n874: │     │                                                                        │\n875: │     ▼                                                                        │\n876: │  ┌──────────────┐                                                            │\n877: │  │ agentcube    │                                                            │\n878: │  │ pack -f .    │                                                            │\n879: │  │ --agent-name │                                                            │\n880: │  │ my-agent     │                                                            │\n881: │  └──────┬───────┘                                                            │\n882: │         │                                                                    │\n883: │         ▼                                                                    │\n884: │  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐                 │\n885: │  │   Parse      │────►│   Create     │────►│   Validate   │                 │\n886: │  │   Options    │     │   PackRuntime│     │   Workspace  │                 │\n887: │  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────┬───────┘                 │\n888: │                                                   │                         │\n889: │                    ┌──────────────────────────────┘                         │\n890: │                    │                                                         │\n891: │                    ▼                                                         │\n892: │  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐                 │\n893: │  │   Apply      │◄────│    Load      │◄────│   Process    │                 │\n894: │  │   Overrides  │     │   Metadata   │     │     Deps     │                 │\n895: │  └──────┬───────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘                 │\n896: │         │                                                                    │\n897: │         ▼                                                                    │\n898: │  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐                 │\n899: │  │   Generate   │────►│   Update     │────►│   Display    │                 │\n900: │  │   Dockerfile │     │   Metadata   │     │   Result     │                 │\n901: │  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘                 │\n902: │                                                   │                          │\n903: │                                                   ▼                          │\n904: │                                          ┌──────────────┐                   │\n905: │                                          │   Success    │                   │\n906: │                                          │   Message    │                   │\n907: │                                          └──────────────┘                   │\n908: │                                                                              │\n909: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n910: ```\n911: \n912: ## Error Handling\n913: \n914: ### Exception Hierarchy\n915: \n916: ```\n917: Exception\n918: ├── ValueError (validation errors)\n919: │   ├── Workspace not found\n920: │   ├── No Python files\n921: │   ├── No pom.xml\n922: │   └── Invalid metadata\n923: ├── FileNotFoundError (missing files)\n924: │   └── Metadata file not found\n925: └── RuntimeError (runtime failures)\n926:     └── Pack operation failed\n927: ```\n928: \n929: ### Error Scenarios\n930: \n931: | Scenario | Error Type | Message |\n932: |----------|------------|---------|\n933: | Missing workspace | ValueError | \"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\" |\n934: | Not a directory | ValueError | \"Workspace path is not a directory: {path}\" |\n935: | No Python files | ValueError | \"No Python files found in workspace\" |\n936: | No pom.xml | ValueError | \"No pom.xml found in workspace (required for Java agents)\" |\n937: | Invalid language | ValueError | \"Unsupported language: {lang}. Must be 'python' or 'java'\" |\n938: | Invalid port | ValueError | \"Invalid port: {port}. Must be between 1 and 65535\" |\n939: | Invalid build_mode | ValueError | \"Unsupported build_mode: {mode}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'\" |\n940: \n941: ## Implementation Notes\n942: \n943: 1. **Metadata Loading**: The system uses a cascading fallback for metadata files:\n944:    - Primary: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n945:    - Fallback 1: `agent.yaml`\n946:    - Fallback 2: `metadata.yaml`\n947:    - Creates new metadata if none found\n948: \n949: 2. **Dockerfile Generation**: Generated Dockerfiles follow language-specific best practices:\n950:    - Python: Uses slim base, proper layer caching\n951:    - Java: Multi-stage build with Maven and JRE\n952: \n953: 3. **Verbose Logging**: When enabled, provides detailed insight into:\n954:    - File discovery\n955:    - Dependency processing\n956:    - Metadata transformations\n957:    - Validation results\n958: \n959: 4. **CLI Override Precedence**: Options provided via CLI take precedence over existing metadata values\n960: \n961: 5. **Rich Progress**: Uses Rich library for beautiful progress indicators during long operations\n\n(End of file - total 961 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 Design: CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-020  \n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe `pack` command is the foundation of the AgentCube CLI toolchain. It validates agent workspace structure, processes metadata, handles dependencies, and optionally generates Dockerfiles to prepare agents for building and publishing. This command is the entry point for the agent lifecycle management workflow.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           Agent Workspace                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Source Files    Metadata    Dependencies    Dockerfile (optional)     │  │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","time":{"start":1775885298721,"end":1775885298734}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885298740,"sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","part":{"id":"prt_d7b03275e001ZU00qQKZ2uyeb0","messageID":"msg_d7b031770001R1UEQ2DXbNd1d4","sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI Pack Command\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-020  \n6: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Implement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI. This command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Pack command options and defaults\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide a `pack` command with well-defined options and sensible defaults.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Default options when pack runs without arguments\n21: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack` without specifying any options\n22: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n23: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n24:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory, from `-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\n25:   - `agent_name` = `None` (from `--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`)\n26:   - `language` = `None` (from `--language`, `Optional[str]`)\n27:   - `entrypoint` = `None` (from `--entrypoint`, `Optional[str]`)\n28:   - `port` = `None` (from `--port`, `Optional[int]`)\n29:   - `build_mode` = `None` (from `--build-mode`, `Optional[str]`)\n30:   - `description` = `None` (from `--description`, `Optional[str]`)\n31:   - `output` = `None` (from `--output`, `Optional[str]`)\n32:   - `verbose` = `False` (from `--verbose`, command-local `bool`)\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Override workspace path\n35: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /path/to/agent`\n36: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n37: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL resolve the workspace path to `/path/to/agent`\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Override agent name\n40: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --agent-name my-custom-agent`\n41: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n42: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `agent_name=\"my-custom-agent\"` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Override language\n45: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --language java`\n46: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n47: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `language=\"java\"` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Override port\n50: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --port 9090`\n51: - **WHEN** the command is executed\n52: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL pass `port=9090` to `PackRuntime.pack()`\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Workspace validation\n57: \n58: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists, is a directory, and contains appropriate source files based on the detected or specified language.\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n61: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /nonexistent/path`\n62: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` is called\n63: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the directory does not exist\n64: - **AND** the CLI SHALL print \"Error packaging agent: {message}\" in red\n65: - **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Workspace path is a file\n68: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack -f /path/to/file.txt` where `file.txt` exists but is not a directory\n69: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` is called\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is not a directory\n71: - **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n74: - **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists\n75: - **AND** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n76: - **WHEN** no `*.py` files exist in the workspace root\n77: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n78: - **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Java workspace without pom.xml\n81: - **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists\n82: - **AND** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n83: - **WHEN** no `pom.xml` file exists in the workspace root\n84: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating Maven project file is missing\n85: - **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Valid Python workspace\n88: - **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists and contains at least one `*.py` file\n89: - **AND** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n90: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n91: - **THEN** no exception SHALL be raised\n92: - **AND** validation SHALL pass\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Valid Java workspace\n95: - **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists and contains `pom.xml`\n96: - **AND** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n97: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n98: - **THEN** no exception SHALL be raised\n99: - **AND** validation SHALL pass\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### Requirement: Metadata management\n104: \n105: The system SHALL load existing metadata, create new metadata if missing, apply CLI option overrides, and persist the final metadata to YAML.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Load existing agent_metadata.yaml\n108: - **GIVEN** the workspace contains `agent_metadata.yaml`\n109: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n110: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the YAML file\n111: - **AND** parse it into an `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n112: - **AND** return the populated `AgentMetadata` instance\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Fallback to agent.yaml\n115: - **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n116: - **AND** the workspace contains `agent.yaml`\n117: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n118: - **THEN** the system SHALL load `agent.yaml`\n119: - **AND** parse it into an `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Fallback to metadata.yaml\n122: - **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml` or `agent.yaml`\n123: - **AND** the workspace contains `metadata.yaml`\n124: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n125: - **THEN** the system SHALL load `metadata.yaml`\n126: - **AND** parse it into an `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Create new metadata when no file exists\n129: - **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain any metadata file\n130: - **AND** no `agent_name` is provided via CLI\n131: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n132: - **THEN** the system SHALL derive the agent name from the workspace directory name\n133: - **AND** create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n134:   - `agent_name` = directory name\n135:   - `language` = `python` (from `MetadataOptions` default)\n136:   - `entrypoint` = inferred from workspace contents\n137:   - `port` = `8080`\n138:   - `build_mode` = `local`\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Apply CLI option overrides\n141: - **GIVEN** existing metadata with `agent_name=\"old-name\"`, `port=8080`\n142: - **AND** CLI options: `--agent-name new-name --port 9090`\n143: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` is called\n144: - **THEN** the returned metadata SHALL have:\n145:   - `agent_name` = `\"new-name\"`\n146:   - `port` = `9090`\n147:   - other fields SHALL remain unchanged from original metadata\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml\n150: - **GIVEN** metadata has been loaded/created and potentially modified\n151: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` is called\n152: - **THEN** the system SHALL write to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n153: - **AND** use `yaml.dump` with:\n154:   - `default_flow_style=False`\n155:   - `indent=2`\n156:   - `sort_keys=False`\n157: - **AND** exclude `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ### Requirement: Language compatibility validation\n162: \n163: The system SHALL validate that the workspace structure is compatible with the specified language.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Supported languages\n166: - **GIVEN** the language field is set to `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n167: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n168: - **THEN** the value SHALL be normalized to lowercase\n169: - **AND** validation SHALL pass\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Unsupported language\n172: - **GIVEN** the language field is set to `\"ruby\"`\n173: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n174: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject the value with validation error\n175: - **AND** raise `ValidationError` with message indicating supported languages are `python` and `java`\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Supported build modes\n178: - **GIVEN** the build_mode field is set to `\"local\"` or `\"cloud\"` (case-insensitive)\n179: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n180: - **THEN** the value SHALL be normalized to lowercase\n181: - **AND** validation SHALL pass\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Unsupported build mode\n184: - **GIVEN** the build_mode field is set to `\"hybrid\"`\n185: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n186: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject the value with validation error\n187: - **AND** raise `ValidationError` with message indicating supported modes are `local` and `cloud`\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Valid port range\n190: - **GIVEN** the port field is set to `8080`\n191: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n192: - **THEN** validation SHALL pass\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Invalid port range\n195: - **GIVEN** the port field is set to `70000` (outside 1-65535)\n196: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run\n197: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject the value with validation error\n198: - **AND** raise `ValidationError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ### Requirement: Entrypoint inference\n203: \n204: The system SHALL infer the entrypoint command when not explicitly provided.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Infer Python entrypoint\n207: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n208: - **AND** the workspace contains `main.py`\n209: - **AND** no entrypoint is specified in metadata or CLI\n210: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` is called\n211: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `python main.py`\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Infer Java entrypoint\n214: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n215: - **AND** the workspace contains `pom.xml`\n216: - **AND** no entrypoint is specified in metadata or CLI\n217: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` is called\n218: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a Maven-based entrypoint\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Cannot infer entrypoint\n221: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n222: - **AND** no clear main file can be identified\n223: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` is called\n224: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a sensible default or raise an appropriate error\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### Requirement: Dependency processing\n229: \n230: The system SHALL process language-specific dependencies as part of the pack operation.\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Process Python dependencies\n233: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n234: - **AND** `metadata.requirements_file` is `requirements.txt`\n235: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_dependencies` is called\n236: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` SHALL be invoked\n237: - **AND** it SHALL validate that `requirements.txt` exists\n238: - **AND** it SHALL log the dependencies being processed if verbose\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: Process Java dependencies\n241: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n242: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_dependencies` is called\n243: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies` SHALL be invoked\n244: - **AND** it SHALL validate Maven project structure\n245: \n246: ---\n247: \n248: ### Requirement: Dockerfile generation\n249: \n250: The system SHALL generate a Dockerfile based on the metadata configuration.\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Generate Python Dockerfile\n253: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n254: - **AND** `metadata.port == 8080`\n255: - **AND** `metadata.entrypoint == \"python main.py\"`\n256: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile` is called\n257: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Dockerfile string containing:\n258:   - `FROM python:3.x-slim` or similar base image\n259:   - `WORKDIR /app`\n260:   - `COPY requirements.txt .` and `RUN pip install`\n261:   - `COPY . .`\n262:   - `EXPOSE 8080`\n263:   - `CMD [\"python\", \"main.py\"]`\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Generate Java Dockerfile\n266: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n267: - **AND** `metadata.port == 8080`\n268: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile` is called\n269: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Dockerfile string containing:\n270:   - Multi-stage build with Maven\n271:   - Build stage compiling the project\n272:   - Runtime stage with JRE\n273:   - `EXPOSE 8080`\n274:   - CMD to run the JAR\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Skip Dockerfile generation when output path is None\n277: - **GIVEN** `output` option is `None`\n278: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime.pack` runs\n279: - **THEN** `_generate_dockerfile` MAY be called\n280: - **AND** the resulting Dockerfile path SHALL be `None`\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ### Requirement: Output path preparation\n285: \n286: The system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n287: \n288: #### Scenario: Default output path\n289: - **GIVEN** `output` option is `None`\n290: - **AND** workspace path is `/home/user/my-agent`\n291: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` is called\n292: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{workspace_path}` (same as input workspace)\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Custom output path\n295: - **GIVEN** `output` option is `/tmp/packed-agent`\n296: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` is called\n297: - **THEN** it SHALL create the directory if it doesn't exist\n298: - **AND** return `Path(\"/tmp/packed-agent\")`\n299: \n300: #### Scenario: Output path is file\n301: - **GIVEN** `output` option points to an existing file (not directory)\n302: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` is called\n303: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the path must be a directory\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ### Requirement: Successful pack operation\n308: \n309: The system SHALL execute a complete pack workflow and report success.\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Complete pack workflow\n312: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace at `/path/to/agent`\n313: - **AND** the workspace contains valid Python files\n314: - **AND** CLI options: `--agent-name my-agent --description \"My agent\"`\n315: - **WHEN** `pack` command completes successfully\n316: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n317:   1. Display a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n318:   2. Call `PackRuntime.pack()` with appropriate options\n319:   3. Validate workspace structure\n320:   4. Load or create metadata\n321:   5. Apply CLI overrides\n322:   6. Validate language compatibility\n323:   7. Process dependencies\n324:   8. Generate Dockerfile (if applicable)\n325:   9. Save updated metadata\n326:   10. Print success message with:\n327:       - `agent_name` = `\"my-agent\"`\n328:       - `workspace_path` = `/path/to/agent`\n329:       - `metadata_path` = `/path/to/agent/agent_metadata.yaml`\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Pack with verbose output\n332: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --verbose`\n333: - **WHEN** the command executes\n334: - **THEN** the system SHALL set logging level to `DEBUG`\n335: - **AND** print detailed logs including:\n336:   - Workspace validation steps\n337:   - Metadata loading/creating steps\n338:   - Override applications\n339:   - Dockerfile generation details\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: Pack failure handling\n344: \n345: The system SHALL handle pack errors gracefully with appropriate error messages.\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: PackRuntime raises exception\n348: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception (e.g., `ValueError(\"Invalid workspace\")`)\n349: - **AND** verbose is `False`\n350: - **WHEN** the pack command catches the exception\n351: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL be called with `(e, \"packing agent\", verbose=False)`\n352: - **AND** the CLI SHALL print `\"Error packaging agent: Invalid workspace\"` in red\n353: - **AND** no traceback SHALL be printed\n354: - **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: PackRuntime raises exception with verbose\n357: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception (e.g., `RuntimeError(\"Docker not available\")`)\n358: - **AND** verbose is `True`\n359: - **WHEN** the pack command catches the exception\n360: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL be called with `(e, \"packing agent\", verbose=True)`\n361: - **AND** the CLI SHALL print `\"Error packaging agent: Docker not available\"` in red\n362: - **AND** a full traceback SHALL be printed\n363: - **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n364: \n365: ---\n366: \n367: ### Requirement: Integration with PackRuntime\n368: \n369: The system SHALL properly instantiate and call `PackRuntime` from the CLI.\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: PackRuntime initialization\n372: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --verbose`\n373: - **WHEN** the pack command handler executes\n374: - **THEN** it SHALL instantiate `PackRuntime(verbose=True)`\n375: \n376: #### Scenario: PackRuntime method call\n377: - **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n378: - **WHEN** the pack command handler executes\n379: - **THEN** it SHALL call `PackRuntime.pack(workspace_path, **options)`\n380: - **AND** pass all relevant options:\n381:   - `agent_name`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port`\n382:   - `build_mode`, `description`, `output`\n383:   - `verbose` (from command-local option)\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: PackRuntime return value\n386: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` returns `{\"agent_name\": \"my-agent\", \"workspace_path\": \"/path/to/agent\", \"metadata_path\": \"/path/to/agent/agent_metadata.yaml\"}`\n387: - **WHEN** the pack command handler receives the result\n388: - **THEN** it SHALL use the returned values for success message formatting\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## Implementation Notes\n393: \n394: ### Error Handling Pattern\n395: All subcommand errors SHALL be handled via `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`:\n396: - Print `\"Error {command_name}: {e}\"` in red (Rich markup)\n397: - If `verbose=True`, print full traceback\n398: - Raise `typer.Exit(1)`\n399: \n400: ### Progress Indication\n401: The pack command SHOULD use Rich `Progress` or spinner during:\n402: - Workspace validation\n403: - Metadata loading/saving\n404: - Dockerfile generation\n405: \n406: ### Metadata Precedence\n407: When loading metadata, the precedence SHALL be:\n408: 1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n409: 2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n410: 3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n411: 4. Create new with defaults (if none exist)\n412: \n413: ### Language Validation\n414: The `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model SHALL validate:\n415: - `language`: must be `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive, normalized to lowercase)\n416: - `build_mode`: must be `\"local\"` or `\"cloud\"` (case-insensitive, normalized to lowercase)\n417: - `port`: must be between 1 and 65535\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n421: ## File Index\n422: \n423: | Path | Purpose |\n424: |------|---------|\n425: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with pack command definition |\n426: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` class implementation |\n427: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model |\n428: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n429: \n430: ---\n431: \n432: ## Dependencies\n433: \n434: | Dependency | Purpose |\n435: |------------|---------|\n436: | `typer` | CLI framework |\n437: | `pydantic` | Data validation for AgentMetadata |\n438: | `pyyaml` | YAML parsing and generation |\n439: | `rich` | Progress indicators and formatted output |\n440: \n441: ---\n442: \n443: ## Related Specifications\n444: \n445: - `cli-toolkit/design.md` — CLI package layout and class definitions\n446: - `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Full CLI specification with all commands\n\n(End of file - total 446 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI Pack Command\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-020  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI. This command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pack command options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `pack` command with well-defined options and sensible defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Default options when pack runs without arguments","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775885298724,"end":1775885298737}}}}
