{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885433708,"sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","part":{"id":"prt_d7b03615a001pZV9MIKHIJo0q0","messageID":"msg_d7b0341ac001mneTbWs7gUpUAS","sessionID":"ses_284fd474bffe6Iq8qLyoLYtY2C","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","content":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-020  \n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n> **Language:** Python  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `pack` command validates agent workspace structure, processes metadata, handles dependencies, and optionally generates Dockerfiles to prepare agents for building and publishing. This command is the entry point for the agent lifecycle management workflow.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Project Structure & Package Setup\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Create `agentcube/__init__.py` with version and exports | File exists; `__version__` defined; imports work | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.2 | Create `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` as subpackage marker | Directory imports work | 0.25h |\n| 4.1.3 | Create `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` with runtime exports | Re-exports PackRuntime, MetadataOptions | 0.25h |\n| 4.1.4 | Create `agentcube/services/__init__.py` with docstring | Package marker with documentation | 0.25h |\n| 4.1.5 | Create `agentcube/models/__init__.py` for model exports | MetadataOptions accessible | 0.25h |\n| 4.1.6 | Create `pyproject.toml` with dependencies and console script | `pip install -e .` works; `kubectl-agentcube` entry point registered | 1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Package structure compiles; `pip install` succeeds.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.2 — Data Models\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.2.1 | Create `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model | Model validates required fields; validators for language/build_mode/port work | 1h |\n| 4.2.2 | Implement `AgentMetadata` validators: `validate_language` | Accepts \"python\"/\"java\"; rejects others; normalizes to lowercase | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.3 | Implement `AgentMetadata` validators: `validate_build_mode` | Accepts \"local\"/\"cloud\"; rejects others; normalizes to lowercase | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.4 | Implement `AgentMetadata` validators: `validate_port` | Accepts 1-65535; rejects out of range | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.5 | Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass | All fields match spec; `from_options()` classmethod works | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.6 | Create `MetadataService` class with `load_metadata()` method | Loads YAML files in precedence order; raises FileNotFoundError if none | 1h |\n| 4.2.7 | Implement `MetadataService.save_metadata()` method | Writes YAML with correct formatting (indent=2, sort_keys=False, exclude_none) | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.8 | Implement `MetadataService.update_metadata()` method | Loads, updates, saves atomically | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Data models validate correctly; service loads/saves metadata.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.3 — PackRuntime Core\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.3.1 | Create `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` with `PackRuntime` class | Class initializes with verbose flag; creates logger | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.2 | Implement `PackRuntime.__init__()` with logger and MetadataService | Logger level set based on verbose; service instantiated | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.3 | Implement `PackRuntime.pack()` main entry point | Returns dict with agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path | 1h |\n| 4.3.4 | Implement `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure()` | Raises ValueError if path doesn't exist or isn't directory | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.5 | Implement `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata()` | Follows precedence: agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml → create new | 1h |\n| 4.3.6 | Implement `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides()` | CLI options override existing metadata values | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.7 | Implement `PackRuntime._validate_language_compatibility()` | Calls language-specific validators | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** PackRuntime validates workspace and handles metadata.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.4 — Language-Specific Validation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.4.1 | Implement `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility()` | Raises ValueError if no *.py files found | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.2 | Implement `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility()` | Raises ValueError if pom.xml not found | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.3 | Implement `MetadataService._validate_python_workspace()` | Same validation logic reusable | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.4 | Implement `MetadataService._validate_java_workspace()` | Same validation logic reusable | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Language validation works for Python and Java workspaces.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.5 — Dependency Processing\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.5.1 | Implement `PackRuntime._process_dependencies()` dispatcher | Calls language-specific processor based on metadata.language | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.2 | Implement `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies()` | Parses requirements.txt; logs dependency count | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.3 | Implement `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies()` | Parses pom.xml; counts Maven dependencies | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.4 | Handle missing requirements.txt gracefully | Logs warning but doesn't fail | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.5 | Handle pom.xml parse errors gracefully | Logs warning on ET.ParseError | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Dependencies processed for both languages with error handling.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.6 — Dockerfile Generation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.6.1 | Implement `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile()` dispatcher | Returns Path or None based on language | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.2 | Implement `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile()` | Returns valid Dockerfile string with correct structure | 1h |\n| 4.6.3 | Implement `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile()` | Returns valid multi-stage Dockerfile with Maven | 1h |\n| 4.6.4 | Implement `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata()` | Sets pack_timestamp, dockerfile_generated; saves metadata | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.5 | Implement `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path()` | Returns Path; handles None output (returns workspace) | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.6 | Implement `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint()` for Python | Detects main.py, app.py, agent.py, or first .py file | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.7 | Implement `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint()` for Java | Returns \"java -jar app.jar\" | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Dockerfiles generated correctly; metadata updated.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.7 — CLI Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.7.1 | Create `agentcube/cli/main.py` with Typer app | App initializes with correct name, help, rich markup | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.2 | Implement `version_callback()` function | Prints version; raises typer.Exit() | 0.25h |\n| 4.7.3 | Implement root callback with `--version` and `--verbose` options | Global verbose enables DEBUG logging | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.4 | Implement `pack` command with all Typer options | All options from design: -f, --agent-name, --language, --entrypoint, --port, --build-mode, --description, --output, --verbose | 1h |\n| 4.7.5 | Implement `_handle_error()` helper | Prints error in red; shows traceback if verbose; exits with code 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.6 | Wire pack command to PackRuntime | Instantiates runtime; calls pack(); handles errors | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.7 | Add Rich progress spinner during pack operation | Progress indicator shown during work | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.8 | Format success message with paths | Prints agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path on success | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** CLI pack command works end-to-end with proper UI.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.8 — Unit Tests — Models\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.8.1 | Write `TestAgentMetadata` — valid Python agent | Model validates with python language | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.2 | Write `TestAgentMetadata` — valid Java agent | Model validates with java language | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.3 | Write `TestAgentMetadata` — language normalization | \"PYTHON\" → \"python\"; \"Java\" → \"java\" | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.4 | Write `TestAgentMetadata` — invalid language rejection | \"ruby\" raises ValidationError | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.5 | Write `TestAgentMetadata` — build_mode validation | \"local\"/\"cloud\" accepted; \"hybrid\" rejected | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.6 | Write `TestAgentMetadata` — port validation | 0 and 70000 rejected; 8080 accepted | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.7 | Write `TestMetadataOptions` — from_options filtering | None values filtered; non-None values preserved | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.8 | Write `TestMetadataService` — load_metadata precedence | agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml | 1h |\n| 4.8.9 | Write `TestMetadataService` — save_metadata formatting | YAML output has correct format | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.10 | Write `TestMetadataService` — file not found | Raises FileNotFoundError when no metadata exists | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Model tests pass with >80% coverage.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.9 — Unit Tests — PackRuntime\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.9.1 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — initialization | Creates logger and MetadataService | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.2 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — validate workspace exists | ValueError on missing path | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.3 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — validate workspace is directory | ValueError on file path | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.4 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — validate Python compatibility | ValueError if no .py files | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.5 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — validate Java compatibility | ValueError if no pom.xml | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.6 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — load existing metadata | Loads from agent_metadata.yaml | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.7 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — create new metadata | Derives name from directory; uses defaults | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.8 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — apply option overrides | CLI options override metadata values | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.9 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — process Python dependencies | Counts requirements.txt entries | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.10 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — process Java dependencies | Counts pom.xml dependencies | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.11 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — generate Python Dockerfile | Content matches expected template | 1h |\n| 4.9.12 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — generate Java Dockerfile | Content matches expected multi-stage template | 1h |\n| 4.9.13 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — infer Python entrypoint | main.py → \"python main.py\" | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.14 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — infer Java entrypoint | Returns \"java -jar app.jar\" | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.15 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — prepare output path | Custom path respected; None returns workspace | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.16 | Write `TestPackRuntime` — pack success | Returns dict with expected keys | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** PackRuntime tests pass with >80% coverage.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.10 — Unit Tests — CLI\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.10.1 | Write `TestCLIPack` — default options | workspace=\".\", verbose=False | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.2 | Write `TestCLIPack` — workspace override | -f /path/to/agent passed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.3 | Write `TestCLIPack` — agent_name override | --agent-name passed to runtime | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.4 | Write `TestCLIPack` — language override | --language java passed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.5 | Write `TestCLIPack` — port override | --port 9090 passed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.6 | Write `TestCLIPack` — error handling non-verbose | Prints error, no traceback, exit 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.7 | Write `TestCLIPack` — error handling verbose | Prints error + traceback, exit 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.8 | Write `TestCLIPack` — version flag | Prints version and exits | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.9 | Write `TestCLIPack` — success output | Success message with paths displayed | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** CLI tests pass with >80% coverage.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.11 — Integration Tests\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.11.1 | Create `tests/integration/test_pack.py` with test workspace fixtures | Temp directories with Python/Java agents | 1h |\n| 4.11.2 | Test complete Python pack workflow | Valid workspace → metadata created → Dockerfile generated | 1h |\n| 4.11.3 | Test complete Java pack workflow | Valid workspace → metadata created → Dockerfile generated | 1h |\n| 4.11.4 | Test pack with existing metadata | Existing agent_metadata.yaml loaded and updated | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.5 | Test pack with CLI overrides | Overrides applied to existing metadata | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.6 | Test pack failure — missing workspace | Error message displayed, exit code 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.7 | Test pack failure — invalid Python workspace | No .py files → error, exit code 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.8 | Test pack failure — invalid Java workspace | No pom.xml → error, exit code 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.9 | Test verbose mode output | DEBUG logs visible during operation | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real filesystem operations.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.12 — Documentation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.12.1 | Add module docstrings to all Python files | `pydoc` shows documentation | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.2 | Document `AgentMetadata` fields with descriptions | Clear field documentation | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.3 | Document `PackRuntime` methods with docstrings | Args, returns, raises documented | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.4 | Add package-level documentation to `agentcube/` | README or docstring overview | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for maintainers.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| ST-4.1: Project Structure | 6 | 3h |\n| ST-4.2: Data Models | 8 | 5h |\n| ST-4.3: PackRuntime Core | 7 | 4.5h |\n| ST-4.4: Language Validation | 4 | 2h |\n| ST-4.5: Dependencies | 5 | 2h |\n| ST-4.6: Dockerfile Generation | 7 | 4.25h |\n| ST-4.7: CLI Implementation | 8 | 4.5h |\n| ST-4.8: Unit Tests — Models | 10 | 5.5h |\n| ST-4.9: Unit Tests — PackRuntime | 16 | 9h |\n| ST-4.10: Unit Tests — CLI | 9 | 4.5h |\n| ST-4.11: Integration Tests | 9 | 5h |\n| ST-4.12: Documentation | 4 | 2h |\n| **Total** | **93** | **51.25h** |\n\n---\n\n## File Deliverables Checklist\n\n- [ ] `pyproject.toml` — Project configuration\n- [ ] `agentcube/__init__.py` — Package exports\n- [ ] `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` — CLI subpackage\n- [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — Typer app and pack command\n- [ ] `agentcube/models/__init__.py` — Models subpackage\n- [ ] `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` — MetadataOptions dataclass\n- [ ] `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` — Runtime exports\n- [ ] `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` — PackRuntime implementation\n- [ ] `agentcube/services/__init__.py` — Services subpackage\n- [ ] `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` — AgentMetadata and MetadataService\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_models.py` — Model unit tests\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_pack_runtime.py` — PackRuntime unit tests\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_cli.py` — CLI unit tests\n- [ ] `tests/integration/test_pack.py` — Integration tests\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n```bash\n# Build/install verification\npip install -e .\n\n# Import verification\npython -c \"from agentcube import PackRuntime; from agentcube.cli.main import app\"\n\n# CLI entry point verification\nkubectl-agentcube --version\nkubectl-agentcube --help\nkubectl-agentcube pack --help\n\n# Unit test verification\npytest tests/unit/ -v\n\n# Model tests\npytest tests/unit/test_models.py -v\n\n# PackRuntime tests\npytest tests/unit/test_pack_runtime.py -v\n\n# CLI tests\npytest tests/unit/test_cli.py -v\n\n# Integration tests\npytest tests/integration/test_pack.py -v\n\n# Coverage report\npytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n\n# Lint verification\nruff check agentcube/\nmypy agentcube/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Definition of Done\n\n- [ ] All 93 tasks complete\n- [ ] Package installs successfully (`pip install -e .`)\n- [ ] CLI entry point works (`kubectl-agentcube`)\n- [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for each module)\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n- [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n- [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0` — CLI framework\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` — YAML parsing\n- `rich>=13.0.0` — Progress indicators and output\n- `packaging>=23.0` — Version handling\n- `semver>=3.0.0` — Semantic versioning\n- `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework\n- `pytest-cov>=4.1.0` — Coverage reporting\n- `pytest-mock>=3.11.0` — Mocking utilities\n\n---\n\n## Design Notes\n\n- **Metadata precedence:** agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml → create new\n- **Language support:** Python and Java (case-insensitive)\n- **Build modes:** local and cloud (case-insensitive)\n- **Dockerfile templates:** Language-specific with best practices\n- **Error handling:** _handle_error() prints red message; traceback on verbose\n- **Progress indication:** Rich Progress spinner during pack operation\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775885433675,"end":1775885433705}}}}
